Dialogue: 0,0:00:01.69,0:00:03.99,Default,,0,0,0,,Welcome, brothers and sisters! \N
Dialogue: 0,0:00:03.99,0:00:06.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Here are some of this month’s highlights: \N
Dialogue: 0,0:00:06.92,0:00:09.43,Default,,0,0,0,,How should we view counsel? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:00:09.43,0:00:11.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Does it apply to us \Neven if we don’t like \N
Dialogue: 0,0:00:11.76,0:00:14.66,Default,,0,0,0,,the way it was given? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:00:14.66,0:00:16.77,Default,,0,0,0,,In times of crisis, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:00:16.77,0:00:21.81,Default,,0,0,0,,how does the organization \Nrespond to help our brothers and sisters? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:00:21.81,0:00:25.58,Default,,0,0,0,,And we will go behind the scenes \Nof last year’s convention drama \N
Dialogue: 0,0:00:25.58,0:00:28.55,Default,,0,0,0,,about King Hezekiah. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:00:28.55,0:00:32.00,Default,,0,0,0,,This is the May program \Nof JW Broadcasting!\N
Dialogue: 0,0:00:51.03,0:00:55.17,Default,,0,0,0,,Let’s begin by visiting a family \Nin Stockholm, Sweden. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:00:55.17,0:00:59.31,Default,,0,0,0,,The parents, Usama and Kristina, \Nhave two daughters, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:00:59.31,0:01:01.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Talita and Isabella. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:01:01.88,0:01:03.91,Default,,0,0,0,,When Talita was born, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:01:03.91,0:01:07.68,Default,,0,0,0,,the doctor found cataracts \Nin both of her eyes. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:01:07.68,0:01:11.76,Default,,0,0,0,,A cataract is a clouding \Nof the eye’s natural lens. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:01:11.76,0:01:13.76,Default,,0,0,0,,So the doctor had to operate \N
Dialogue: 0,0:01:13.76,0:01:16.89,Default,,0,0,0,,so that Talita wouldn’t lose \Nher sight completely\N
Dialogue: 0,0:01:16.89,0:01:20.00,Default,,0,0,0,,—a terrifying situation \Nfor any parent. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:01:21.03,0:01:23.47,Default,,0,0,0,,Today, Talita is seven years old \N
Dialogue: 0,0:01:23.47,0:01:25.90,Default,,0,0,0,,and almost blind in one eye \N
Dialogue: 0,0:01:25.90,0:01:28.00,Default,,0,0,0,,but completely blind in the other. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:01:29.07,0:01:31.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Teaching a child about Jehovah \N
Dialogue: 0,0:01:31.07,0:01:33.54,Default,,0,0,0,,in this system of things \Nis already a challenge \N
Dialogue: 0,0:01:33.54,0:01:36.91,Default,,0,0,0,,even without physical ailments involved. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:01:36.91,0:01:41.35,Default,,0,0,0,,But let’s find out how Talita’s parents \Nrose to the challenge, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:01:41.35,0:01:45.29,Default,,0,0,0,,making sure that she received \Na proper spiritual education \N
Dialogue: 0,0:01:45.29,0:01:47.00,Default,,0,0,0,,despite her poor vision.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:01:52.86,0:01:56.47,Default,,0,0,0,,I look forward to not having \Npoor sight anymore \N
Dialogue: 0,0:01:56.47,0:01:59.47,Default,,0,0,0,,and that I can play \Nwith a bear and a lion \N
Dialogue: 0,0:01:59.47,0:02:02.00,Default,,0,0,0,,and to sit \Non the back of a tiger.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:03.77,0:02:08.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Jehovah gives us \Na fantastic promise at Isaiah 35:5: \N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:08.61,0:02:11.00,Default,,0,0,0,,“The eyes of the blind will be opened.”\N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:12.72,0:02:17.29,Default,,0,0,0,,It’s been a challenge \Nto get to where we are today. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:17.29,0:02:20.00,Default,,0,0,0,,We thank Jehovah \Nfor all the help he has given us.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:21.02,0:02:25.20,Default,,0,0,0,,As soon as Talita was able \Nto leave the house after the operation, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:25.20,0:02:28.00,Default,,0,0,0,,we made sure \Nto go to the meetings.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:29.80,0:02:33.00,Default,,0,0,0,,It helped us a lot to be able \Nto throw our burden on Jehovah. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:34.70,0:02:36.87,Default,,0,0,0,,We prayed together; \N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:36.87,0:02:39.00,Default,,0,0,0,,we cried a lot together \Nbecause it was so hard.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:44.18,0:02:46.18,Default,,0,0,0,,One of the challenges \N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:46.18,0:02:50.32,Default,,0,0,0,,is that we have to give \NTalita audio description constantly. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:50.32,0:02:54.00,Default,,0,0,0,,We have to tell her who is coming in \Nand what is happening.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:55.49,0:02:59.86,Default,,0,0,0,,We get so many amazing materials \Non jw.org \N
Dialogue: 0,0:02:59.86,0:03:02.00,Default,,0,0,0,,and also through the congregation. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:03.60,0:03:06.00,Default,,0,0,0,,She really loves to read \NLearn From the Great Teacher. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:07.24,0:03:12.00,Default,,0,0,0,,It has questions \Nwhich make her a part of the story.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:14.01,0:03:15.85,Default,,0,0,0,,She has a very good memory, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:15.85,0:03:19.12,Default,,0,0,0,,and therefore she remembers \Na lot of what she reads. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:19.12,0:03:23.00,Default,,0,0,0,,So when we are with friends, \Nshe often quizzes them.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:53.62,0:03:56.00,Default,,0,0,0,,I really like to sing \Nthe songs in my songbook.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:03:58.49,0:04:00.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Talita’s spiritual goal\N
Dialogue: 0,0:04:00.46,0:04:04.83,Default,,0,0,0,,is to learn more \Nof our Kingdom songs. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:04:04.83,0:04:06.83,Default,,0,0,0,,We get so much help \N
Dialogue: 0,0:04:06.83,0:04:09.97,Default,,0,0,0,,from the beautiful music \Non the website \N
Dialogue: 0,0:04:09.97,0:04:13.00,Default,,0,0,0,,and also \Nfrom the Caleb and Sophia videos.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:04:15.84,0:04:19.04,Default,,0,0,0,,She knows many of the stories\Nfrom My Book of Bible Stories,\N
Dialogue: 0,0:04:19.04,0:04:21.81,Default,,0,0,0,,so she can answer in her own words. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:04:21.81,0:04:25.28,Default,,0,0,0,,We will ask a question like, \NDo you know this about David? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:04:25.28,0:04:27.15,Default,,0,0,0,,And if she knows the answer, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:04:27.15,0:04:30.00,Default,,0,0,0,,then we encourage her \Nto answer at the meeting.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:04:36.26,0:04:38.43,Default,,0,0,0,,When I give an answer \Nat the meetings, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:04:38.43,0:04:39.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Jehovah becomes happy \N
Dialogue: 0,0:04:39.80,0:04:42.97,Default,,0,0,0,,because he loves children.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:04:42.97,0:04:45.20,Default,,0,0,0,,She often asks the friends, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:04:45.20,0:04:46.67,Default,,0,0,0,,“Do you love Jehovah?” \N
Dialogue: 0,0:04:46.67,0:04:49.00,Default,,0,0,0,,So she feels very united with them.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:04:53.11,0:04:55.24,Default,,0,0,0,,One of the best moments where we saw \N
Dialogue: 0,0:04:55.24,0:04:57.68,Default,,0,0,0,,that Talita’s spirituality had grown \N
Dialogue: 0,0:04:57.68,0:05:00.05,Default,,0,0,0,,was when she came home from a sleepover \N
Dialogue: 0,0:05:00.05,0:05:02.05,Default,,0,0,0,,at her grandparents’ house. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:05:02.05,0:05:04.69,Default,,0,0,0,,My parents are not Jehovah’s Witnesses, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:05:04.69,0:05:06.32,Default,,0,0,0,,and her grandmother had said \N
Dialogue: 0,0:05:06.32,0:05:08.26,Default,,0,0,0,,that God doesn’t exist. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:05:08.26,0:05:11.13,Default,,0,0,0,,So when Talita came home, she said, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:05:11.13,0:05:14.03,Default,,0,0,0,,“And then when I was going to sleep, \NI prayed to Jehovah,\N
Dialogue: 0,0:05:14.03,0:05:16.00,Default,,0,0,0,,“‘Would you please help Grandmother \N
Dialogue: 0,0:05:16.00,0:05:19.00,Default,,0,0,0,,to realize that you do exist\N—that you are real?’”\N
Dialogue: 0,0:05:23.47,0:05:27.08,Default,,0,0,0,,We try to keep \Nour wonderful hope alive, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:05:27.08,0:05:30.18,Default,,0,0,0,,so we often talk  about \Nwhat we will do \N
Dialogue: 0,0:05:30.18,0:05:32.42,Default,,0,0,0,,in Paradise. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:05:32.42,0:05:36.22,Default,,0,0,0,,We really look forward to when Talita \Nwill be able to see again \N
Dialogue: 0,0:05:36.22,0:05:39.16,Default,,0,0,0,,and live in a paradise \Nwith all our friends. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:05:39.16,0:05:42.00,Default,,0,0,0,,It’s going to be wonderful!\N
Dialogue: 0,0:05:43.39,0:05:46.40,Default,,0,0,0,,I think that Jehovah \Nlooks forward to looking at me \N
Dialogue: 0,0:05:46.40,0:05:49.00,Default,,0,0,0,,when I play with a tiger.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:05:52.74,0:05:56.64,Default,,0,0,0,,I’ll have to make sure that I remember \Nthe names of Joseph’s brothers \N
Dialogue: 0,0:05:56.64,0:06:00.81,Default,,0,0,0,,in case I meet Talita \Nand she decides to quiz me! \N
Dialogue: 0,0:06:00.81,0:06:05.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Her parents have done a good job \Nin raising such a fine young sister. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:06:05.65,0:06:07.65,Default,,0,0,0,,And together with them, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:06:07.65,0:06:11.42,Default,,0,0,0,,we eagerly look forward \Nto the benefits of the new system. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:06:11.42,0:06:14.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Isaiah 35:5 says: \N
Dialogue: 0,0:06:14.36,0:06:19.00,Default,,0,0,0,,“At that time the eyes \Nof the blind will be opened.”\N
Dialogue: 0,0:06:20.26,0:06:24.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Such divine reminders \Ncan truly warm our heart. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:06:24.07,0:06:27.77,Default,,0,0,0,,And Jehovah’s reminders \Nnot only provide us comfort \N
Dialogue: 0,0:06:27.77,0:06:31.14,Default,,0,0,0,,but can also help us \Nmake important decisions \N
Dialogue: 0,0:06:31.14,0:06:33.14,Default,,0,0,0,,in our everyday life. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:06:33.14,0:06:37.65,Default,,0,0,0,,This brings us to our music video \Nwhich is entitled \N
Dialogue: 0,0:06:37.65,0:06:40.00,Default,,0,0,0,,I Keep Your Reminders.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:06:56.20,0:07:07.94,Default,,0,0,0,,What should I do? \NWho should I look to?\N
Dialogue: 0,0:07:07.94,0:07:12.00,Default,,0,0,0,,This could just be harmless, \Ncould be respectable.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:07:14.48,0:07:19.00,Default,,0,0,0,,There may be no need \Nfor me to reject it all.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:07:20.12,0:07:29.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, what is the right course for me? \NWhich path will it be?\N
Dialogue: 0,0:07:32.07,0:07:43.95,Default,,0,0,0,,What should I do? \NTake which point of view?\N
Dialogue: 0,0:07:43.95,0:07:48.00,Default,,0,0,0,,It could be excessive, \Nwith many dangers there—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:07:50.49,0:07:56.43,Default,,0,0,0,,All the kinds of things \Nthat could prove to be a snare.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:07:56.43,0:08:06.87,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, what is the right course for me? \NJehovah, give ear to my plea.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:08:06.87,0:08:13.44,Default,,0,0,0,,I keep your reminders, \Nand I love them dearly.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:08:13.44,0:08:19.38,Default,,0,0,0,,I’ll treasure them every day, \Nmonthly, yearly.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:08:19.38,0:08:28.00,Default,,0,0,0,,All the things I have heard in accord \Nwith your Word, help me understand.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:08:33.56,0:08:44.00,Default,,0,0,0,,I know what’s required. \NI’d better inquire.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:08:46.34,0:08:51.88,Default,,0,0,0,,I don’t want to act \Nin a way to cause offense,\N
Dialogue: 0,0:08:51.88,0:08:58.55,Default,,0,0,0,,But it sounds like \Nthere likely would be consequence.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:08:58.55,0:09:09.00,Default,,0,0,0,,It’s clear what’s the right course for me\N—the key, the guarantee.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:09:09.00,0:09:14.60,Default,,0,0,0,,I keep your reminders, \Nand I love them dearly.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:09:14.60,0:09:21.08,Default,,0,0,0,,They strengthen my heart \Nand help me to see clearly.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:09:21.08,0:09:30.00,Default,,0,0,0,,All the things I have heard in accord\Nwith your Word, help me understand.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:09:53.58,0:10:00.42,Default,,0,0,0,,I keep your reminders, \Nand I love them dearly.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:10:00.42,0:10:06.76,Default,,0,0,0,,They strengthen my heart \Nand help me to see clearly.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:10:06.76,0:10:12.66,Default,,0,0,0,,As I read day and night, \Nmy life fills up with light.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:10:12.66,0:10:19.60,Default,,0,0,0,,I’ve got you by my side \Nas I think of your might.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:10:19.60,0:10:27.00,Default,,0,0,0,,All the things I have heard in accord \Nwith your Word, help me understand.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:10:33.45,0:10:36.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Did you notice \Nthat it was a Bible-trained conscience \N
Dialogue: 0,0:10:36.62,0:10:39.86,Default,,0,0,0,,that helped our sister \Nmake a wise decision? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:10:39.86,0:10:43.36,Default,,0,0,0,,She knew what potential danger \Nlay ahead. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:10:43.36,0:10:47.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, the reminders \Nfrom God’s Word guided her.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:10:47.86,0:10:50.77,Default,,0,0,0,,The theme for our program this month is \N
Dialogue: 0,0:10:50.77,0:10:53.87,Default,,0,0,0,,“Treasure Jehovah’s Reminders.” \N
Dialogue: 0,0:10:53.87,0:10:58.31,Default,,0,0,0,,And it’s based on Psalm 19:7, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:10:58.31,0:11:00.71,Default,,0,0,0,,where we’re told: \N
Dialogue: 0,0:11:00.71,0:11:04.61,Default,,0,0,0,,“The reminder of Jehovah is trustworthy, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:11:04.61,0:11:08.00,Default,,0,0,0,,making the inexperienced one wise.”\N
Dialogue: 0,0:11:09.19,0:11:13.49,Default,,0,0,0,,In the original language, \Nthe word here translated as “reminder” \N
Dialogue: 0,0:11:13.49,0:11:18.00,Default,,0,0,0,,comes from a root word meaning \N“to go over again, to repeat.” \N
Dialogue: 0,0:11:19.10,0:11:23.37,Default,,0,0,0,,Reminders have always been \Nan essential part of Jehovah’s teaching. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:11:23.37,0:11:27.14,Default,,0,0,0,,In ancient Israel, \NGod’s people continually received \N
Dialogue: 0,0:11:27.14,0:11:31.34,Default,,0,0,0,,commandments, \Nregulations, and reminders. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:11:31.34,0:11:33.51,Default,,0,0,0,,In fact, Jehovah tells us \N
Dialogue: 0,0:11:33.51,0:11:36.61,Default,,0,0,0,,that he sent \Nhis prophets “again and again” \N
Dialogue: 0,0:11:36.61,0:11:41.00,Default,,0,0,0,,to repeatedly remind his people \Nof their responsibilities.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:11:42.02,0:11:45.02,Default,,0,0,0,,The apostle Peter \Nfelt the need to give reminders \N
Dialogue: 0,0:11:45.02,0:11:48.72,Default,,0,0,0,,even to those \Nwho were “well-established in the truth.” \N
Dialogue: 0,0:11:48.72,0:11:50.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Notice how he describes this \N
Dialogue: 0,0:11:50.69,0:11:54.86,Default,,0,0,0,,at 2 Peter 1:12, 13: \N
Dialogue: 0,0:11:54.86,0:11:58.40,Default,,0,0,0,,“For this reason I intend always \N
Dialogue: 0,0:11:58.40,0:12:00.34,Default,,0,0,0,,“to remind you of these things, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:12:00.34,0:12:03.24,Default,,0,0,0,,“although you know them \Nand are well-established \N
Dialogue: 0,0:12:03.24,0:12:05.37,Default,,0,0,0,,“in the truth that is present in you. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:12:05.37,0:12:07.54,Default,,0,0,0,,“But I consider it right, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:12:07.54,0:12:09.98,Default,,0,0,0,,“as long as I am in this tabernacle, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:12:09.98,0:12:12.00,Default,,0,0,0,,to stir you with reminders.” \N
Dialogue: 0,0:12:13.55,0:12:16.62,Default,,0,0,0,,In verse 15, \Nhe goes on to give the reason \N
Dialogue: 0,0:12:16.62,0:12:19.62,Default,,0,0,0,,why he felt the need \Nto give the brothers reminders. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:12:19.62,0:12:21.66,Default,,0,0,0,,He says: \N
Dialogue: 0,0:12:21.66,0:12:26.46,Default,,0,0,0,,“I will always do my utmost \Nso that after my departure, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:12:26.46,0:12:30.00,Default,,0,0,0,,you may be able to recall \Nthese things for yourselves.” \N
Dialogue: 0,0:12:31.33,0:12:34.27,Default,,0,0,0,,So Peter was determined \Nto help the brothers and sisters\N
Dialogue: 0,0:12:34.27,0:12:37.44,Default,,0,0,0,, in his day to remember, or recall, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:12:37.44,0:12:40.61,Default,,0,0,0,,the teachings they had already learned. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:12:40.61,0:12:42.71,Default,,0,0,0,,It shouldn’t come as a surprise, then, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:12:42.71,0:12:46.42,Default,,0,0,0,,if today a lot of our teaching \Ninvolves reminders. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:12:46.42,0:12:50.32,Default,,0,0,0,,It follows the pattern set \Nby Jehovah in ancient Israel \N
Dialogue: 0,0:12:50.32,0:12:53.72,Default,,0,0,0,,and with the first-century Christians.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:12:53.72,0:12:56.43,Default,,0,0,0,,But why do we need reminders? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:12:56.43,0:12:59.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Let’s consider three reasons. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:12:59.36,0:13:04.03,Default,,0,0,0,,First, let’s look at Psalm 103:2. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:13:04.03,0:13:06.04,Default,,0,0,0,,There it says: \N
Dialogue: 0,0:13:06.04,0:13:08.44,Default,,0,0,0,,“Let me praise Jehovah; \N
Dialogue: 0,0:13:08.44,0:13:11.00,Default,,0,0,0,,may I never forget all that he has done.” \N
Dialogue: 0,0:13:12.24,0:13:14.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Why, then, do we need reminders? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:13:14.54,0:13:17.58,Default,,0,0,0,,Simply put, because we forget. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:13:17.58,0:13:19.72,Default,,0,0,0,,If we had perfect memories, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:13:19.72,0:13:22.22,Default,,0,0,0,,we wouldn’t need so many reminders. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:13:22.22,0:13:25.39,Default,,0,0,0,,Even in everyday life, \Nmany of us use little notes\N
Dialogue: 0,0:13:25.39,0:13:28.26,Default,,0,0,0,,to remind ourselves \Nof what we need to do. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:13:28.26,0:13:30.69,Default,,0,0,0,,And who of us \Nhasn’t seen the need \N
Dialogue: 0,0:13:30.69,0:13:33.56,Default,,0,0,0,,for a list of reminders \Nwhen going shopping, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:13:33.56,0:13:36.43,Default,,0,0,0,,only to realize when we returned \N
Dialogue: 0,0:13:36.43,0:13:39.24,Default,,0,0,0,,that we forgot to get one \Nof the important items \N
Dialogue: 0,0:13:39.24,0:13:41.24,Default,,0,0,0,,we needed to purchase? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:13:41.24,0:13:44.27,Default,,0,0,0,,If reminders are important \Nin everyday life, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:13:44.27,0:13:46.28,Default,,0,0,0,,how much more so in matters \N
Dialogue: 0,0:13:46.28,0:13:49.91,Default,,0,0,0,,that involve our relationship \Nwith Jehovah.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:13:49.91,0:13:54.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Let’s read Luke 10:39, 40. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:13:55.28,0:13:57.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Speaking of Martha, we are told:\N
Dialogue: 0,0:13:57.82,0:14:00.86,Default,,0,0,0,,“She also had a sister called Mary, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:14:00.86,0:14:03.23,Default,,0,0,0,,“who sat down at the feet of the Lord \N
Dialogue: 0,0:14:03.23,0:14:05.93,Default,,0,0,0,,“and kept listening to what he was saying. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:14:05.93,0:14:07.93,Default,,0,0,0,,“Martha, on the other hand, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:14:07.93,0:14:11.00,Default,,0,0,0,,was distracted\Nwith attending to many duties.” \N
Dialogue: 0,0:14:12.74,0:14:14.64,Default,,0,0,0,,What was Martha’s problem? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:14:14.64,0:14:16.67,Default,,0,0,0,,She was distracted. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:14:16.67,0:14:19.81,Default,,0,0,0,,So the second reason \Nwhy we need reminders \N
Dialogue: 0,0:14:19.81,0:14:24.41,Default,,0,0,0,,is that, like Martha, \Nat times we too become distracted. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:14:24.41,0:14:27.35,Default,,0,0,0,,Although we may already know \Na vital fact, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:14:27.35,0:14:30.32,Default,,0,0,0,,that fact might get put \Ninto the back of our mind, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:14:30.32,0:14:31.82,Default,,0,0,0,,figuratively speaking, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:14:31.82,0:14:34.00,Default,,0,0,0,,because other matters \Nare demanding our attention. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:14:36.13,0:14:39.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Satan is the great Distracter. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:14:39.06,0:14:43.57,Default,,0,0,0,,He tries to turn our attention away \Nfrom the true issues of our day. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:14:43.57,0:14:47.27,Default,,0,0,0,,People in general have become \Nmore and more distracted \N
Dialogue: 0,0:14:47.27,0:14:51.31,Default,,0,0,0,,by entertainment \Nand other nonessential matters. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:14:51.31,0:14:55.78,Default,,0,0,0,,No wonder that Satan \Nhas succeeded in misleading so many. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:14:55.78,0:14:58.00,Default,,0,0,0,,They don’t even realize \Nwhat has happened.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:14:59.62,0:15:03.09,Default,,0,0,0,,Reason number three \Nis alluded to \N
Dialogue: 0,0:15:03.09,0:15:06.39,Default,,0,0,0,,at Matthew 24:45: \N
Dialogue: 0,0:15:06.39,0:15:09.93,Default,,0,0,0,,“Who really \Nis the faithful and discreet slave \N
Dialogue: 0,0:15:09.93,0:15:12.70,Default,,0,0,0,,“whom his master appointed \Nover his domestics, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:15:12.70,0:15:16.87,Default,,0,0,0,,to give them their food \Nat the proper time?” \N
Dialogue: 0,0:15:16.87,0:15:21.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Notice that the spiritual food \Nis given to us “at the proper time.” \N
Dialogue: 0,0:15:21.57,0:15:25.47,Default,,0,0,0,,Our circumstances in life \Nare continually changing. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:15:25.47,0:15:27.48,Default,,0,0,0,,How often do we hear, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:15:27.48,0:15:29.78,Default,,0,0,0,,“That was just what I needed?” \N
Dialogue: 0,0:15:29.78,0:15:32.00,Default,,0,0,0,,We’ve all experienced that, \Nhaven’t we?\N
Dialogue: 0,0:15:33.15,0:15:36.69,Default,,0,0,0,,So, what are three of the reasons \Nwhy we need reminders? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:15:36.69,0:15:40.26,Default,,0,0,0,,One, \Nbecause we tend to forget things. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:15:40.26,0:15:43.83,Default,,0,0,0,,Two, \Nwe often become distracted. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:15:43.83,0:15:47.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Three, \Nour changed circumstances \N
Dialogue: 0,0:15:47.06,0:15:50.57,Default,,0,0,0,,may require a reminder \Nof something we already knew \N
Dialogue: 0,0:15:50.57,0:15:53.00,Default,,0,0,0,,but didn’t fully need at that time.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:15:54.14,0:15:57.04,Default,,0,0,0,,So that brings us to the next question: \N
Dialogue: 0,0:15:57.04,0:15:59.54,Default,,0,0,0,,What will help us to remember? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:15:59.54,0:16:04.08,Default,,0,0,0,,It’s interesting to note \Nthat Jehovah has used many ways \N
Dialogue: 0,0:16:04.08,0:16:07.02,Default,,0,0,0,,to remind his people \Nof what they should do. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:16:07.02,0:16:10.65,Default,,0,0,0,,At Numbers 10:10, we’re told\N
Dialogue: 0,0:16:10.65,0:16:14.02,Default,,0,0,0,,that the various festivals \Nwere given as reminders, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:16:14.02,0:16:17.96,Default,,0,0,0,,especially the celebration \Nof the Passover. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:16:17.96,0:16:20.36,Default,,0,0,0,,That means \Nthat every time the Israelites \N
Dialogue: 0,0:16:20.36,0:16:23.37,Default,,0,0,0,,prepared and celebrated \None of these festivals, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:16:23.37,0:16:26.20,Default,,0,0,0,,they were reminded \Nof important matters, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:16:26.20,0:16:29.51,Default,,0,0,0,,such as how Jehovah \Nprovides for his people \N
Dialogue: 0,0:16:29.51,0:16:32.88,Default,,0,0,0,,and how he has saved them \Nin the past. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:16:32.88,0:16:35.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Something similar happens today \N
Dialogue: 0,0:16:35.04,0:16:37.91,Default,,0,0,0,,at the commemoration \Nof the Lord’s Evening Meal. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:16:37.91,0:16:41.75,Default,,0,0,0,,Not only do we hear \Nthe reminders from God’s Word \N
Dialogue: 0,0:16:41.75,0:16:44.95,Default,,0,0,0,,but the act of passing \Nthe bread and wine \N
Dialogue: 0,0:16:44.95,0:16:47.96,Default,,0,0,0,,also serves as an action\Nthat reminds us \N
Dialogue: 0,0:16:47.96,0:16:50.00,Default,,0,0,0,,of what Jesus did in our behalf.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:16:51.43,0:16:54.83,Default,,0,0,0,,But what do we need to do\Nin order for those reminders\N
Dialogue: 0,0:16:54.83,0:16:57.00,Default,,0,0,0,,to have a beneficial impact \Non our lives? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:16:58.37,0:17:03.87,Default,,0,0,0,,Notice what Psalm 119:99 says. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:17:03.87,0:17:05.01,Default,,0,0,0,,It tells us: \N
Dialogue: 0,0:17:05.01,0:17:08.78,Default,,0,0,0,,“I have more insight than all my teachers, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:17:08.78,0:17:12.78,Default,,0,0,0,,because I ponder over your reminders.” \N
Dialogue: 0,0:17:12.78,0:17:15.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, we need to ponder \Nover these reminders. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:17:15.78,0:17:19.56,Default,,0,0,0,,That means not just \Nlistening to or reading them, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:17:19.56,0:17:22.73,Default,,0,0,0,,but it involves thinking deeply \Nabout them— \N
Dialogue: 0,0:17:22.73,0:17:24.93,Default,,0,0,0,,meditating on their value. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:17:24.93,0:17:28.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Just to listen or read  without meditating \N
Dialogue: 0,0:17:28.30,0:17:31.30,Default,,0,0,0,,is like looking through the lens \Nof a movie camera \N
Dialogue: 0,0:17:31.30,0:17:34.10,Default,,0,0,0,,without pressing the record button. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:17:34.10,0:17:36.74,Default,,0,0,0,,We see things and hear things, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:17:36.74,0:17:39.78,Default,,0,0,0,,but nothing is recorded. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:17:39.78,0:17:43.05,Default,,0,0,0,,So we need \Nto meditate, visualize, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:17:43.05,0:17:45.41,Default,,0,0,0,,and review these reminders. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:17:45.41,0:17:48.75,Default,,0,0,0,,This will help us \Nto remember what we learn.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:17:48.75,0:17:52.35,Default,,0,0,0,,But, figuratively speaking, \Nthere is something else \N
Dialogue: 0,0:17:52.35,0:17:55.52,Default,,0,0,0,,that we can do \Nto press the record button. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:17:55.52,0:17:58.03,Default,,0,0,0,,That means we don’t have to wait \N
Dialogue: 0,0:17:58.03,0:18:00.33,Default,,0,0,0,,for someone else \Nto give us a reminder. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:18:00.33,0:18:03.20,Default,,0,0,0,,We can make our own reminder. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:18:03.20,0:18:05.93,Default,,0,0,0,,How can we do so? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:18:05.93,0:18:08.17,Default,,0,0,0,,The answer to that question \N
Dialogue: 0,0:18:08.17,0:18:11.64,Default,,0,0,0,,is highlighted \Nin Jehovah’s instructions to Moses \N
Dialogue: 0,0:18:11.64,0:18:15.14,Default,,0,0,0,,as found at Exodus 17:14: \N
Dialogue: 0,0:18:15.14,0:18:17.78,Default,,0,0,0,,“Jehovah now said to Moses: \N
Dialogue: 0,0:18:17.78,0:18:20.68,Default,,0,0,0,,“‘Write this as a memorial \N
Dialogue: 0,0:18:20.68,0:18:22.85,Default,,0,0,0,,“‘[or the footnote says: “reminder”] \N
Dialogue: 0,0:18:22.85,0:18:25.52,Default,,0,0,0,,in the book and repeat it to Joshua.’” \N
Dialogue: 0,0:18:25.52,0:18:27.52,Default,,0,0,0,,What’s the point? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:18:27.52,0:18:31.93,Default,,0,0,0,,Write down new things \Nwe want to remember. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:18:31.93,0:18:35.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Some brothers use a notebook, \Nor exercise book, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:18:35.10,0:18:39.03,Default,,0,0,0,,to write down a list of interesting points \Nthat they want to remember. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:18:39.03,0:18:42.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Then they look through the book \Nfrom time to time \N
Dialogue: 0,0:18:42.00,0:18:45.04,Default,,0,0,0,,to remind themselves of those points. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:18:45.04,0:18:49.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Many of us do this with our notes \Nfrom conventions and assemblies. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:18:49.65,0:18:52.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Of course, to do that successfully, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:18:52.28,0:18:55.05,Default,,0,0,0,,you need to remember \Nwhere you put the notebook. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:18:55.05,0:18:57.35,Default,,0,0,0,,Additionally, \Nwe have to be careful \N
Dialogue: 0,0:18:57.35,0:19:00.62,Default,,0,0,0,,that we don’t write down \Nevery little fact. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:19:00.62,0:19:05.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Otherwise, we may become overwhelmed \Nwith all the information.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:19:06.16,0:19:08.63,Default,,0,0,0,,We can make \Nthese notes either on paper \N
Dialogue: 0,0:19:08.63,0:19:13.54,Default,,0,0,0,,or electronically using computers \Nor electronic devices. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:19:13.54,0:19:17.47,Default,,0,0,0,,Whatever system we use, \Nlet’s make lists of things \N
Dialogue: 0,0:19:17.47,0:19:19.00,Default,,0,0,0,,that we want to remember. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:19:20.51,0:19:24.85,Default,,0,0,0,,Many brothers have found it good \Nto have two separate lists. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:19:24.85,0:19:27.62,Default,,0,0,0,,One list could be subjects\N
Dialogue: 0,0:19:27.62,0:19:29.65,Default,,0,0,0,,—perhaps points that we want to use \N
Dialogue: 0,0:19:29.65,0:19:32.79,Default,,0,0,0,,in the ministry or in our own lives. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:19:32.79,0:19:35.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Another, scriptures\N
Dialogue: 0,0:19:35.12,0:19:40.00,Default,,0,0,0,,—explanations that clarify \Nthe meaning of certain verses.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:19:40.00,0:19:42.76,Default,,0,0,0,,With regard to notes on scriptures, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:19:42.76,0:19:45.80,Default,,0,0,0,,let’s ask a very important question: \N
Dialogue: 0,0:19:45.80,0:19:49.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Do you have a study Bible? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:19:49.34,0:19:52.01,Default,,0,0,0,,What is a study Bible? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:19:52.01,0:19:54.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Perhaps it’s a separate Bible \N
Dialogue: 0,0:19:54.08,0:19:56.35,Default,,0,0,0,,to the one you take in the ministry. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:19:56.35,0:19:58.91,Default,,0,0,0,,It’s a Bible for you to write in \N
Dialogue: 0,0:19:58.91,0:20:01.00,Default,,0,0,0,,so that you’re reminded \Nof things that you’ve learned. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:20:02.58,0:20:07.26,Default,,0,0,0,,These are some of the things \Nwe can do with a study Bible: \N
Dialogue: 0,0:20:07.26,0:20:10.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Highlight or underline some words or verses. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:20:10.69,0:20:13.56,Default,,0,0,0,,That will make it easier to find them again. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:20:13.56,0:20:17.30,Default,,0,0,0,,But remember not to make \Ntoo many highlights or marks; \N
Dialogue: 0,0:20:17.30,0:20:20.47,Default,,0,0,0,,otherwise, nothing will stand out. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:20:20.47,0:20:23.97,Default,,0,0,0,,Write a summary of points and scriptures \Nyou want to remember \N
Dialogue: 0,0:20:23.97,0:20:28.88,Default,,0,0,0,,on the blank pages in the front \Nor the back of your Bible. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:20:28.88,0:20:30.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Write notes in the margin\N
Dialogue: 0,0:20:30.98,0:20:33.68,Default,,0,0,0,,—that’s what Gilead students often do. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:20:33.68,0:20:37.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Of course, you need \Nthe right type of pen or pencil \N
Dialogue: 0,0:20:37.02,0:20:40.76,Default,,0,0,0,,that won’t bleed through \Nto the other side of the page. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:20:40.76,0:20:44.16,Default,,0,0,0,,What type of things \Ncould you write in the margin? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:20:44.16,0:20:47.83,Default,,0,0,0,,Perhaps new points \Nthat you learn while reading magazines \N
Dialogue: 0,0:20:47.83,0:20:50.47,Default,,0,0,0,,or attending meetings and assemblies. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:20:50.47,0:20:53.94,Default,,0,0,0,,If you learn a new point, ask yourself, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:20:53.94,0:20:56.37,Default,,0,0,0,,‘What verse is being explained?’ \N
Dialogue: 0,0:20:56.37,0:21:01.21,Default,,0,0,0,,And then write a brief comment \Nin the margin next to that verse.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:21:01.21,0:21:03.21,Default,,0,0,0,,Let’s take an example. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:21:03.21,0:21:06.21,Default,,0,0,0,,Perhaps you are reading \Nthe Sermon on the Mount \N
Dialogue: 0,0:21:06.21,0:21:10.59,Default,,0,0,0,,and you get to Matthew 7:24-27. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:21:10.59,0:21:12.59,Default,,0,0,0,,That’s the illustration \N
Dialogue: 0,0:21:12.59,0:21:15.26,Default,,0,0,0,,about the two men who built houses\N
Dialogue: 0,0:21:15.26,0:21:18.19,Default,,0,0,0,,—one on sand and the other on rock. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:21:18.19,0:21:21.20,Default,,0,0,0,,As you research this \Nin Watchtower Library \N
Dialogue: 0,0:21:21.20,0:21:23.20,Default,,0,0,0,,or the Research Guide, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:21:23.20,0:21:25.20,Default,,0,0,0,,you come across the article \N
Dialogue: 0,0:21:25.20,0:21:27.94,Default,,0,0,0,,“Are You Building on Sand or on Rock?” \N
Dialogue: 0,0:21:27.94,0:21:31.00,Default,,0,0,0,,in the November 1, 2008, Watchtower. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:21:32.54,0:21:34.68,Default,,0,0,0,,What points could you write in the margin \N
Dialogue: 0,0:21:34.68,0:21:37.15,Default,,0,0,0,,to help you remember the explanation? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:21:37.15,0:21:39.21,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, perhaps you could write: \N
Dialogue: 0,0:21:39.21,0:21:43.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Sand equals build on the surface. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:21:43.69,0:21:48.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Rock equals dig down deep. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:21:48.42,0:21:52.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Digging equals doing and applying. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:21:52.76,0:21:57.13,Default,,0,0,0,,You might even put Luke 6:46-48 there. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:21:57.13,0:22:00.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, if you still have room \Nand your writing is small, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:22:00.57,0:22:02.70,Default,,0,0,0,,you could add something like this: \N
Dialogue: 0,0:22:02.70,0:22:06.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Not hearers only, but doers. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:22:06.54,0:22:09.91,Default,,0,0,0,,Both houses in same location, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:22:09.91,0:22:14.55,Default,,0,0,0,,same tests, foundations different. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:22:14.55,0:22:17.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Now every time \Nyou read those verses, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:22:17.12,0:22:20.39,Default,,0,0,0,,you will be reminded \Nof what they mean.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:22:20.39,0:22:22.39,Default,,0,0,0,,Perhaps like me, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:22:22.39,0:22:25.53,Default,,0,0,0,,you’ve had several study Bibles \Nover the years. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:22:25.53,0:22:27.90,Default,,0,0,0,,I think back to the first one I used. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:22:27.90,0:22:30.50,Default,,0,0,0,,It was like this big green Bible. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:22:30.50,0:22:34.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Then, later that was replaced \Nby another Bible\N
Dialogue: 0,0:22:34.50,0:22:36.94,Default,,0,0,0,,—this black covered Bible. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:22:36.94,0:22:39.04,Default,,0,0,0,,And then, further still, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:22:39.04,0:22:42.78,Default,,0,0,0,,we had another Bible\N—the Reference Bible. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:22:42.78,0:22:45.48,Default,,0,0,0,,And, of course, \Nnow for most of us, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:22:45.48,0:22:48.65,Default,,0,0,0,,we have the large-print Bible.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:22:48.65,0:22:51.09,Default,,0,0,0,,This does, however, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:22:51.09,0:22:53.49,Default,,0,0,0,,highlight a challenge \Nwe might experience. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:22:53.49,0:22:55.29,Default,,0,0,0,,It can be frustrating \N
Dialogue: 0,0:22:55.29,0:22:57.89,Default,,0,0,0,,when a new edition \Nof the Bible comes out. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:22:57.89,0:23:00.23,Default,,0,0,0,,How do you transfer all your study notes \N
Dialogue: 0,0:23:00.23,0:23:02.30,Default,,0,0,0,,over to the new Bible? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:23:02.30,0:23:06.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Additionally, our beloved study Bible \Nmay wear out \N
Dialogue: 0,0:23:06.84,0:23:12.00,Default,,0,0,0,,or, worse still, be lost, stolen, burned, \Nruined, run over, blown away. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:23:14.04,0:23:18.21,Default,,0,0,0,,So that’s the advantage \Nof using an electronic list; \N
Dialogue: 0,0:23:18.21,0:23:21.25,Default,,0,0,0,,it doesn’t matter \Nwhat type of file you use. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:23:21.25,0:23:25.75,Default,,0,0,0,,It can be updated very easily, \Nand you can even make copies\N
Dialogue: 0,0:23:25.75,0:23:27.76,Default,,0,0,0,,—not like the printed copy \N
Dialogue: 0,0:23:27.76,0:23:31.39,Default,,0,0,0,,that already has \Nthe old idea written in the margin. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:23:31.39,0:23:33.83,Default,,0,0,0,,Even now in English, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:23:33.83,0:23:36.60,Default,,0,0,0,,we have the books \Nof Matthew, Mark, and Luke \N
Dialogue: 0,0:23:36.60,0:23:38.87,Default,,0,0,0,,in our electronic study Bible \N
Dialogue: 0,0:23:38.87,0:23:42.44,Default,,0,0,0,,on jw.org and WOL. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:23:42.44,0:23:46.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Later in the program, \Nwe have some exciting news \N
Dialogue: 0,0:23:46.31,0:23:49.54,Default,,0,0,0,,about how JW Library \Nwill help us in this regard. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:23:49.54,0:23:52.98,Default,,0,0,0,,But I’ll leave that for later.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:23:52.98,0:23:57.45,Default,,0,0,0,,Really, having a study Bible \Nis not only helpful \N
Dialogue: 0,0:23:57.45,0:24:01.66,Default,,0,0,0,,but it also makes our personal study \Nfar more interesting. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:24:01.66,0:24:03.66,Default,,0,0,0,,How so? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:24:03.66,0:24:07.23,Default,,0,0,0,,Every time we read \Nor study a publication, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:24:07.23,0:24:10.23,Default,,0,0,0,,we’ll find ourselves \Nsearching for new points \N
Dialogue: 0,0:24:10.23,0:24:13.47,Default,,0,0,0,,that we can write \Nin our study Bible. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:24:13.47,0:24:16.87,Default,,0,0,0,,This way, we’ll be doing \Nwhat the psalmist expressed \N
Dialogue: 0,0:24:16.87,0:24:20.38,Default,,0,0,0,,at Psalm 119:111: \N
Dialogue: 0,0:24:20.38,0:24:22.78,Default,,0,0,0,,‘We will take Jehovah’s reminders \N
Dialogue: 0,0:24:22.78,0:24:25.95,Default,,0,0,0,,‘as our permanent possession \N(or heritage), \N
Dialogue: 0,0:24:25.95,0:24:30.00,Default,,0,0,0,,for his reminders \Nare the joy of our hearts!’\N
Dialogue: 0,0:24:31.49,0:24:35.19,Default,,0,0,0,,But do you agree that sometimes \Nthe reminders we get \N
Dialogue: 0,0:24:35.19,0:24:37.66,Default,,0,0,0,,may be less than pleasant? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:24:37.66,0:24:40.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Maybe they even hurt! \N
Dialogue: 0,0:24:40.20,0:24:42.56,Default,,0,0,0,,In this dramatization, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:24:42.56,0:24:46.00,Default,,0,0,0,,pay attention to how \Nwe should respond to counsel.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:24:59.85,0:25:02.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Today started out well.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:25:09.19,0:25:11.06,Default,,0,0,0,,But after the meeting tonight, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:25:11.06,0:25:14.00,Default,,0,0,0,,my feelings were hurt.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:25:22.54,0:25:25.74,Default,,0,0,0,,Earlier in the week, we invited \Nsome friends over to watch a movie.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:25:25.74,0:25:27.81,Default,,0,0,0,,And apparently, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:25:27.81,0:25:30.00,Default,,0,0,0,,this new young elder heard about it, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:25:31.11,0:25:33.82,Default,,0,0,0,,so he counseled me about it \Nafter the meeting, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:25:33.82,0:25:36.25,Default,,0,0,0,,saying that I should give \Nmy movie choices \N
Dialogue: 0,0:25:36.25,0:25:38.65,Default,,0,0,0,,some thought.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:25:38.65,0:25:41.66,Default,,0,0,0,,I just didn’t like \Nthe way he gave the counsel. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:25:41.66,0:25:43.73,Default,,0,0,0,,He’s only 27. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:25:43.73,0:25:46.00,Default,,0,0,0,,That’s too young.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:25:50.60,0:25:54.00,Default,,0,0,0,,The next day, \Nwe had plans to go out in the ministry \N
Dialogue: 0,0:25:54.00,0:25:57.94,Default,,0,0,0,,with Brother Kang and his wife.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:25:57.94,0:25:59.34,Default,,0,0,0,,But the motivation \N
Dialogue: 0,0:25:59.34,0:26:02.00,Default,,0,0,0,,just wasn’t there.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:26:13.36,0:26:16.36,Default,,0,0,0,,I asked to speak \Nwith Brother Kang alone. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:26:16.36,0:26:18.36,Default,,0,0,0,,I told him what happened \N
Dialogue: 0,0:26:18.36,0:26:22.20,Default,,0,0,0,,and how we didn’t feel \Nthe counsel applied to us.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:26:22.20,0:26:24.70,Default,,0,0,0,,I can understand \Nhow you might feel. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:26:24.70,0:26:26.13,Default,,0,0,0,,But, Byong Soo, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:26:26.13,0:26:28.50,Default,,0,0,0,,be absolutely honest with me. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:26:28.50,0:26:33.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Do you feel there is no valid reason \Nfor that counsel?\N
Dialogue: 0,0:26:33.31,0:26:36.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Mm. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:26:42.35,0:26:44.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, maybe there were some scenes \N
Dialogue: 0,0:26:44.69,0:26:46.99,Default,,0,0,0,,that could have been less violent. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:26:46.99,0:26:49.16,Default,,0,0,0,,But the way he gave the counsel\N
Dialogue: 0,0:26:49.16,0:26:51.36,Default,,0,0,0,,—he didn’t even ask how we felt.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:26:51.36,0:26:54.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Byong Soo, what is the only way \N
Dialogue: 0,0:26:54.30,0:26:56.50,Default,,0,0,0,,for us to receive perfect counsel?\N
Dialogue: 0,0:26:56.50,0:26:58.73,Default,,0,0,0,,From a perfect man.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:26:58.73,0:27:00.67,Default,,0,0,0,,That’s right. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:27:00.67,0:27:04.91,Default,,0,0,0,,And is Jesus here on the earth today?\N
Dialogue: 0,0:27:04.91,0:27:07.24,Default,,0,0,0,,He was right. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:27:07.24,0:27:09.81,Default,,0,0,0,,Counsel can only be perfect \N
Dialogue: 0,0:27:09.81,0:27:12.00,Default,,0,0,0,,if it’s given from a perfect person.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:27:13.48,0:27:17.35,Default,,0,0,0,,Still, this counsel \Nabout our movie choices \N
Dialogue: 0,0:27:17.35,0:27:19.59,Default,,0,0,0,,would have been so much easier \N
Dialogue: 0,0:27:19.59,0:27:23.53,Default,,0,0,0,,if it came from someone older \Nand more experienced, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:27:23.53,0:27:26.00,Default,,0,0,0,,like Brother Kang.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:27:27.53,0:27:31.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, he must have sensed \Nwhat I was thinking \N
Dialogue: 0,0:27:31.00,0:27:33.23,Default,,0,0,0,,because he helped me to remember \N
Dialogue: 0,0:27:33.23,0:27:36.00,Default,,0,0,0,,something from the Bible.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:27:37.71,0:27:40.38,Default,,0,0,0,,When Job underwent severe trials, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:27:40.38,0:27:43.55,Default,,0,0,0,,it was the younger Elihu who helped Job \N
Dialogue: 0,0:27:43.55,0:27:46.00,Default,,0,0,0,,adjust his thinking correctly.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:27:47.78,0:27:50.92,Default,,0,0,0,,It required humility on Job’s part \N
Dialogue: 0,0:27:50.92,0:27:54.00,Default,,0,0,0,,to listen to someone younger \Nand less experienced.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:27:57.03,0:27:59.93,Default,,0,0,0,,He then read Proverbs 19:20: \N
Dialogue: 0,0:27:59.93,0:28:04.20,Default,,0,0,0,,“Listen to counsel and accept discipline, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:28:04.20,0:28:09.60,Default,,0,0,0,,in order to become wise in your future.”\N
Dialogue: 0,0:28:09.60,0:28:11.61,Default,,0,0,0,,The point was clear: \N
Dialogue: 0,0:28:11.61,0:28:14.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Keep our focus on the counsel, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:28:14.64,0:28:17.00,Default,,0,0,0,,not the counselor.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:28:30.33,0:28:34.00,Default,,0,0,0,,I later shared \NBrother Kang’s comments with my wife. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:28:35.10,0:28:38.00,Default,,0,0,0,,We both realized that we should welcome \N
Dialogue: 0,0:28:38.00,0:28:40.74,Default,,0,0,0,,all counsel from Jehovah. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:28:40.74,0:28:42.00,Default,,0,0,0,,It’s for our good.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:29:02.62,0:29:05.76,Default,,0,0,0,,I’m sure it took courage \N
Dialogue: 0,0:29:05.76,0:29:09.00,Default,,0,0,0,,for that young elder \Nto approach me about the matter. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:29:10.13,0:29:13.10,Default,,0,0,0,,But I’m so glad he did because, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:29:13.10,0:29:15.64,Default,,0,0,0,,in the end, his counsel \N
Dialogue: 0,0:29:15.64,0:29:18.44,Default,,0,0,0,,was just another example \N
Dialogue: 0,0:29:18.44,0:29:20.00,Default,,0,0,0,,of God’s love.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:29:23.14,0:29:25.75,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, we all need reminders. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:29:25.75,0:29:28.35,Default,,0,0,0,,And did you notice some \Nof the main teaching points \N
Dialogue: 0,0:29:28.35,0:29:30.35,Default,,0,0,0,,in this dramatization? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:29:30.35,0:29:32.62,Default,,0,0,0,,First, \Nwe need to be humble \N
Dialogue: 0,0:29:32.62,0:29:34.62,Default,,0,0,0,,when we receive counsel. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:29:34.62,0:29:38.73,Default,,0,0,0,,Second, \Nwe need to keep our focus on the counsel, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:29:38.73,0:29:40.76,Default,,0,0,0,,not the counselor. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:29:40.76,0:29:44.70,Default,,0,0,0,,And the young elder likely learned \Nfrom the experience too. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:29:44.70,0:29:48.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Perhaps next time, \Nafter conferring with a seasoned elder, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:29:48.60,0:29:53.00,Default,,0,0,0,,he might handle matters \Nwith a little bit more tact and discretion. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:29:54.24,0:29:58.51,Default,,0,0,0,,But we can’t rely solely \Non receiving reminders from others \N
Dialogue: 0,0:29:58.51,0:30:00.95,Default,,0,0,0,,to keep our spirituality intact. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:30:00.95,0:30:03.28,Default,,0,0,0,,We need to do our part.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:30:03.28,0:30:05.29,Default,,0,0,0,,One of the tools that can help us \N
Dialogue: 0,0:30:05.29,0:30:07.72,Default,,0,0,0,,to actively search out reminders \N
Dialogue: 0,0:30:07.72,0:30:09.89,Default,,0,0,0,,is JW Library. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:30:09.89,0:30:13.03,Default,,0,0,0,,This amazing app has been installed \N
Dialogue: 0,0:30:13.03,0:30:16.73,Default,,0,0,0,,on over 15 million devices. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:30:16.73,0:30:19.37,Default,,0,0,0,,But do you know \Nhow much work it takes \N
Dialogue: 0,0:30:19.37,0:30:21.74,Default,,0,0,0,,to develop and maintain this app? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:30:21.74,0:30:25.81,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, we are now going  to look \Nbehind the scenes \N
Dialogue: 0,0:30:25.81,0:30:29.91,Default,,0,0,0,,and meet some of the brothers \Nwho have either worked on this project \N
Dialogue: 0,0:30:29.91,0:30:32.35,Default,,0,0,0,,or helped to organize that work. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:30:32.35,0:30:35.02,Default,,0,0,0,,This really is an opportunity to visit \N
Dialogue: 0,0:30:35.02,0:30:39.09,Default,,0,0,0,,an area in Bethel \Nthat you don’t get to see on tour. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:30:39.09,0:30:42.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Of course, there are many brothers \Nassociated with the work. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:30:42.96,0:30:46.23,Default,,0,0,0,,But we would like you \Nto get to know three \N
Dialogue: 0,0:30:46.23,0:30:48.30,Default,,0,0,0,,of these very hard-working brothers, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:30:48.30,0:30:51.00,Default,,0,0,0,,and let me introduce them to you. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:30:51.00,0:30:55.54,Default,,0,0,0,,First of all, Brother Per Christensen, \Nthe overseer of MEPS Programming. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:30:55.54,0:30:57.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, Per, you’ve been in this country \N
Dialogue: 0,0:30:57.07,0:30:59.84,Default,,0,0,0,,working in the U.S. Bethel \Nfor a number of years. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:30:59.84,0:31:01.00,Default,,0,0,0,,But where are you from originally?\N
Dialogue: 0,0:31:02.11,0:31:04.05,Default,,0,0,0,,I was born in Denmark \N
Dialogue: 0,0:31:04.05,0:31:07.25,Default,,0,0,0,,and served there in the branch for years.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:31:07.25,0:31:11.62,Default,,0,0,0,,So when did you and your wife, Berit, \Ncome to the United States?\N
Dialogue: 0,0:31:11.62,0:31:13.15,Default,,0,0,0,,In 1994. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:31:13.15,0:31:15.69,Default,,0,0,0,,And our first year was in Brooklyn. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:31:15.69,0:31:18.26,Default,,0,0,0,,And then we had 18 years in Patterson \N
Dialogue: 0,0:31:18.26,0:31:21.26,Default,,0,0,0,,and then back to Brooklyn again \Nfor three and a half years. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:31:21.26,0:31:25.60,Default,,0,0,0,,And now we’re in Warwick \Nsince November last year.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:31:25.60,0:31:28.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, I know you worked \Nin Translation Services for a while \N
Dialogue: 0,0:31:28.64,0:31:30.71,Default,,0,0,0,,because, in fact, \Nthe two of us worked together \N
Dialogue: 0,0:31:30.71,0:31:32.31,Default,,0,0,0,,in the same department \Nthere for a while. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:31:32.31,0:31:35.81,Default,,0,0,0,,But what type of work \Nhave you been involved with \N
Dialogue: 0,0:31:35.81,0:31:37.98,Default,,0,0,0,,since you’ve come \Nto the United States?\N
Dialogue: 0,0:31:37.98,0:31:41.58,Default,,0,0,0,,Lots of exciting and challenging jobs. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:31:41.58,0:31:43.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Working in Translation Services\N
Dialogue: 0,0:31:43.82,0:31:48.79,Default,,0,0,0,,—that was training and support \Nfor our translators worldwide. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:31:48.79,0:31:50.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Now in MEPS Programming\N
Dialogue: 0,0:31:50.86,0:31:54.20,Default,,0,0,0,,—that is all about \Ndistribution of spiritual food \N
Dialogue: 0,0:31:54.20,0:31:56.50,Default,,0,0,0,,to all our brothers and sisters. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:31:56.50,0:32:00.80,Default,,0,0,0,,So we have a ton of work \Nand a lot of challenges. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:32:00.80,0:32:02.90,Default,,0,0,0,,But I’m also working with a lot \N
Dialogue: 0,0:32:02.90,0:32:06.31,Default,,0,0,0,,of very, very talented \Nbrothers and sisters. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:32:06.31,0:32:10.98,Default,,0,0,0,,So it’s a lot of fun, \Nand it’s great going to work every day.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:32:10.98,0:32:12.55,Default,,0,0,0,,That’s great to hear, Per. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:32:12.55,0:32:15.72,Default,,0,0,0,,In fact, I’m even tempted \Nto come back and work with you.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:32:15.72,0:32:16.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, we would love that.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:32:16.72,0:32:18.72,Default,,0,0,0,,I think I’d love it too.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:32:18.72,0:32:22.39,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, let’s turn our attention \Nto Brother Alfredo Serna. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:32:22.39,0:32:25.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, you are the assistant overseer \Nof MEPS Programming. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:32:25.26,0:32:29.96,Default,,0,0,0,,In fact, you and I worked together \Nin Mexico back in 2003. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:32:29.96,0:32:33.43,Default,,0,0,0,,Could you tell us a little bit \Nabout what you were doing at that time?\N
Dialogue: 0,0:32:33.43,0:32:35.67,Default,,0,0,0,,My last work assignment involved overseeing \N
Dialogue: 0,0:32:35.67,0:32:37.91,Default,,0,0,0,,the large Translation Department there. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:32:37.91,0:32:39.97,Default,,0,0,0,,It was an amazing privilege to work \N
Dialogue: 0,0:32:39.97,0:32:43.71,Default,,0,0,0,,with translators in sign language \Nand the indigenous languages, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:32:43.71,0:32:47.75,Default,,0,0,0,,a true joy to contribute\Nto preparing publications \N
Dialogue: 0,0:32:47.75,0:32:49.88,Default,,0,0,0,,for those in the minority groups.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:32:49.88,0:32:53.49,Default,,0,0,0,,So when did you and your wife, Gina, \Ncome to the United States to work here?\N
Dialogue: 0,0:32:53.49,0:32:56.86,Default,,0,0,0,,We arrived at Patterson in 2007. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:32:56.86,0:32:58.86,Default,,0,0,0,,We have fond memories of that time, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:32:58.86,0:33:01.06,Default,,0,0,0,,and it’s something we still treasure.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:33:01.06,0:33:01.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Very good. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:33:01.86,0:33:04.93,Default,,0,0,0,,And now, \NBrother Paul Willies, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:33:04.93,0:33:08.30,Default,,0,0,0,,where do you originally come from \Nalong with your wife, Su-lin, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:33:08.30,0:33:11.14,Default,,0,0,0,,and when did you come\Nto the United States?\N
Dialogue: 0,0:33:11.14,0:33:13.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, we’re both originally \Nfrom South Africa, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:33:13.54,0:33:15.54,Default,,0,0,0,,and we served there in Bethel \Nfor a number of years. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:33:15.54,0:33:18.71,Default,,0,0,0,,And then in 2010, \Nwe were transferred to work \N
Dialogue: 0,0:33:18.71,0:33:21.32,Default,,0,0,0,,along with MEPS Programming \Nhere in the U.S.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:33:21.32,0:33:24.09,Default,,0,0,0,,So, what type of work \Nhave you been involved with, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:33:24.09,0:33:26.09,Default,,0,0,0,,particularly recently?\N
Dialogue: 0,0:33:26.09,0:33:27.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, most of my time in Bethel \N
Dialogue: 0,0:33:27.46,0:33:29.76,Default,,0,0,0,,I’ve been working \Non the Watchtower Translation System, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:33:29.76,0:33:31.26,Default,,0,0,0,,or WTS. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:33:31.26,0:33:33.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Actually, \NI was working along with Per. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:33:33.26,0:33:35.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Per was in headquarters, \Nand I was working \N
Dialogue: 0,0:33:35.10,0:33:37.97,Default,,0,0,0,,on the programming team \Nthat we had in South Africa. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:33:37.97,0:33:40.27,Default,,0,0,0,,WTS is the program \Nthat the translators use \N
Dialogue: 0,0:33:40.27,0:33:42.40,Default,,0,0,0,,to help organize and manage \Ntheir translation work. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:33:42.40,0:33:46.01,Default,,0,0,0,,And then, of course, most recently \NI’ve been working on the mobile apps\N
Dialogue: 0,0:33:46.01,0:33:49.71,Default,,0,0,0,,—the JW Library app \Nand the JW Library Sign Language app.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:33:49.71,0:33:50.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Very good. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:33:50.88,0:33:53.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, now all of you work \Nin MEPS Programming. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:33:53.61,0:33:56.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Per, can you just tell us a little bit? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:33:56.22,0:33:59.45,Default,,0,0,0,,We’re familiar with the term MEPS, \Nbut what really is it?\N
Dialogue: 0,0:33:59.45,0:34:01.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, MEPS stands for \N
Dialogue: 0,0:34:01.46,0:34:05.09,Default,,0,0,0,,Multilanguage Electronic Publishing System.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:34:05.09,0:34:06.46,Default,,0,0,0,,That didn’t help me at all. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:34:06.46,0:34:07.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Sorry. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:34:07.63,0:34:10.23,Default,,0,0,0,,Can you make it a little bit \Nmore simple so we can understand?\N
Dialogue: 0,0:34:10.23,0:34:14.54,Default,,0,0,0,,We make the tools, or the programs, \Nthat the organization needs \N
Dialogue: 0,0:34:14.54,0:34:17.00,Default,,0,0,0,,to make publications \N
Dialogue: 0,0:34:17.00,0:34:21.58,Default,,0,0,0,,and have them translated \Ninto hundreds of languages. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:34:21.58,0:34:24.21,Default,,0,0,0,,So I can illustrate it this way:\N
Dialogue: 0,0:34:24.21,0:34:26.95,Default,,0,0,0,,that we are not making \Nthe spiritual food, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:34:26.95,0:34:30.79,Default,,0,0,0,,but we are building \Na conveyor belt for the spiritual food \N
Dialogue: 0,0:34:30.79,0:34:33.32,Default,,0,0,0,,from the faithful and discreet slave \N
Dialogue: 0,0:34:33.32,0:34:35.69,Default,,0,0,0,,down to the printing presses \N
Dialogue: 0,0:34:35.69,0:34:38.76,Default,,0,0,0,,or to our website \Nor to Watchtower Library, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:34:38.76,0:34:42.86,Default,,0,0,0,,ONLINE LIBRARY \Nor, like in this case, JW Library.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:34:42.86,0:34:44.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Thanks so much. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:34:44.03,0:34:45.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, at long last, I do understand \Na bit more \N
Dialogue: 0,0:34:45.90,0:34:47.90,Default,,0,0,0,,about what MEPS means. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:34:47.90,0:34:51.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, as I travel around, \Nthe brothers and sisters, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:34:51.44,0:34:54.41,Default,,0,0,0,,they tell me how much \Nthey love JW Library. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:34:54.41,0:34:57.08,Default,,0,0,0,,But there seems to be no end \N
Dialogue: 0,0:34:57.08,0:35:00.18,Default,,0,0,0,,to the suggestions \Nfor improvements and features\N
Dialogue: 0,0:35:00.18,0:35:02.72,Default,,0,0,0,,—and long lists of suggestions. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:35:02.72,0:35:06.85,Default,,0,0,0,,Can you give us a little bit \Nof an idea of what’s involved \N
Dialogue: 0,0:35:06.85,0:35:10.00,Default,,0,0,0,,with trying to develop \Na new feature for JW Library?\N
Dialogue: 0,0:35:11.33,0:35:14.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, the brothers and the sisters \Nreally love using the app, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:35:14.53,0:35:18.13,Default,,0,0,0,,and because of that, \Nthey’re keen to get many new features. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:35:18.13,0:35:22.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Of course, we wish we could just add \Nall those new features into the app, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:35:22.27,0:35:25.34,Default,,0,0,0,,but the truth is we just can’t.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:35:25.34,0:35:28.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, adding each new feature \Ninvolves a lot of work. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:35:28.84,0:35:32.08,Default,,0,0,0,,And we also need to determine \Nwhether a feature \N
Dialogue: 0,0:35:32.08,0:35:34.08,Default,,0,0,0,,that’s requested is just a “nice to have” \N
Dialogue: 0,0:35:34.08,0:35:37.19,Default,,0,0,0,,or is it something \Nthat’s going to address a real need? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:35:37.19,0:35:40.92,Default,,0,0,0,,For example, will it really help an elder \Nwho is out on a shepherding call \N
Dialogue: 0,0:35:40.92,0:35:44.09,Default,,0,0,0,,or maybe a pioneer sister \Nwho is at the public witnessing carts \N
Dialogue: 0,0:35:44.09,0:35:46.89,Default,,0,0,0,,or at her Bible study or return visit? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:35:46.89,0:35:50.77,Default,,0,0,0,,Also, very important \Nto us is trying to make \N
Dialogue: 0,0:35:50.77,0:35:53.94,Default,,0,0,0,,each new feature \Nvery simple to use . . .\N
Dialogue: 0,0:35:53.94,0:35:55.37,Default,,0,0,0,,Ah, thanks for doing that.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:35:55.37,0:35:59.04,Default,,0,0,0,,. . . especially for a first-time user, \Nsomeone who’s never used the app before. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:35:59.04,0:36:01.61,Default,,0,0,0,,And then, of course, \Nbefore we start working on anything, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:36:01.61,0:36:03.48,Default,,0,0,0,,we always get approval \Nfrom the Governing Body.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:36:03.48,0:36:05.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Ah, that’s a good thing to do too.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:36:05.31,0:36:08.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Like one feature \Nthat many have been asking for \N
Dialogue: 0,0:36:08.52,0:36:12.09,Default,,0,0,0,,is the ability \Nto add notes into the app. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:36:12.09,0:36:14.76,Default,,0,0,0,,And, of course, \Nbefore we start programming it, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:36:14.76,0:36:18.46,Default,,0,0,0,,we have to make sure \Nthat it actually does what is wanted. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:36:18.46,0:36:21.00,Default,,0,0,0,,We made a video \Nthat shows how we go about that.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:36:21.00,0:36:21.63,Default,,0,0,0,,You have?\N
Dialogue: 0,0:36:21.63,0:36:22.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Would you like to see it?\N
Dialogue: 0,0:36:22.26,0:36:25.33,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, of course. \NI’d love to see it!\N
Dialogue: 0,0:36:25.33,0:36:26.83,Default,,0,0,0,,Hello. \NHow are you?\N
Dialogue: 0,0:36:26.83,0:36:27.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Good, good, good.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:36:27.67,0:36:28.87,Default,,0,0,0,,Welcome! \NThanks for coming.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:36:28.87,0:36:29.94,Default,,0,0,0,,How about yourself? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:36:29.94,0:36:30.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Fine, thank you. \NHave a seat. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:36:30.67,0:36:32.67,Default,,0,0,0,,All right, so glad you could be here! \N
Dialogue: 0,0:36:32.67,0:36:33.91,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you so much.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:36:33.91,0:36:35.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, so fancy.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:36:35.11,0:36:38.25,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah!\NSo we get to talk about JW Library today. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:36:38.25,0:36:41.08,Default,,0,0,0,,So, what are some ways \Nthat you use JW Library?\N
Dialogue: 0,0:36:41.08,0:36:44.09,Default,,0,0,0,,I mean, it’s revolutionized \Ngoing to meetings.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:36:44.09,0:36:45.05,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, my.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:36:45.05,0:36:47.29,Default,,0,0,0,,I go to meetings \Nand sometimes I just carry my iPad.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:36:47.29,0:36:49.39,Default,,0,0,0,,So the fact that you can make \Nthe text larger. . .\N
Dialogue: 0,0:36:49.39,0:36:52.56,Default,,0,0,0,,It’s easy to listen \Nto the readings right in the app now, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:36:52.56,0:36:54.26,Default,,0,0,0,,and so I—I find myself doing that.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:36:54.26,0:36:56.30,Default,,0,0,0,,So if we were \Nto make a notes feature, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:36:56.30,0:36:58.60,Default,,0,0,0,,what are some things \Nthat you’d like to be able to do?\N
Dialogue: 0,0:36:58.60,0:37:00.90,Default,,0,0,0,,I mean, if you could see \Nall your notes without tapping on \N
Dialogue: 0,0:37:00.90,0:37:02.00,Default,,0,0,0,,each one that would be great.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:37:03.37,0:37:06.87,Default,,0,0,0,,And even if you make a note in, \Nmaybe, your phone \N
Dialogue: 0,0:37:06.87,0:37:09.54,Default,,0,0,0,,and it can also be saved in your tablet, \Nthat would be really nice.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:37:09.54,0:37:10.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:37:10.08,0:37:13.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, what if I told you \Nthat in front of you  \N
Dialogue: 0,0:37:13.65,0:37:16.75,Default,,0,0,0,,is an early version of JW Library?\N
Dialogue: 0,0:37:16.75,0:37:17.25,Default,,0,0,0,,Whoa! \NCool!\N
Dialogue: 0,0:37:17.25,0:37:18.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, fantastic!\N
Dialogue: 0,0:37:18.15,0:37:18.75,Default,,0,0,0,,This is it?\N
Dialogue: 0,0:37:18.75,0:37:20.15,Default,,0,0,0,,With notes—yeah.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:37:20.15,0:37:22.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Ooh.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:37:22.19,0:37:24.43,Default,,0,0,0,,So a few months ago, \Nthe Governing Body \N
Dialogue: 0,0:37:24.43,0:37:26.69,Default,,0,0,0,,gave us approval to start working \Non the notes feature. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:37:26.69,0:37:30.03,Default,,0,0,0,,We got together as a team, \Nand we’ll do, like, these rough sketches, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:37:30.03,0:37:31.57,Default,,0,0,0,,and programmers write code. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:37:31.57,0:37:33.00,Default,,0,0,0,,But before we release an update, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:37:33.00,0:37:34.14,Default,,0,0,0,,we have a group of testers. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:37:34.14,0:37:36.60,Default,,0,0,0,,And, you know, they’ll find \Nlittle glitches or bugs or things, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:37:36.60,0:37:38.51,Default,,0,0,0,,but they’ll try to work it out \Nwith the programmers. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:37:38.51,0:37:42.38,Default,,0,0,0,,After that, we have \Na pretty stable version of JW Library. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:37:42.38,0:37:44.28,Default,,0,0,0,,The goal is to show it to you, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:37:44.28,0:37:47.35,Default,,0,0,0,,and you can let us know \Nwhat you think.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:37:47.35,0:37:49.78,Default,,0,0,0,,So now that you’ve seen \Nthe new notes feature \N
Dialogue: 0,0:37:49.78,0:37:51.39,Default,,0,0,0,,in JW Library, what do you think?\N
Dialogue: 0,0:37:51.39,0:37:55.89,Default,,0,0,0,,I love that I can tag the personal things \Nthat I need to work on \N
Dialogue: 0,0:37:55.89,0:37:58.19,Default,,0,0,0,,or a comment or a scripture \Nthat I can encourage someone with. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:37:58.19,0:37:59.19,Default,,0,0,0,,This is fantastic!\N
Dialogue: 0,0:37:59.19,0:38:00.09,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah. \NIt’s great. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:38:00.09,0:38:03.97,Default,,0,0,0,,I like that I can find my notes, \Nespecially using the search feature. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:38:03.97,0:38:04.73,Default,,0,0,0,,It’s great!\N
Dialogue: 0,0:38:04.73,0:38:07.03,Default,,0,0,0,,And it’s really neat \Nhow my comments— \N
Dialogue: 0,0:38:07.03,0:38:09.54,Default,,0,0,0,,I can place it right next \Nto the paragraph for meetings, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:38:09.54,0:38:11.74,Default,,0,0,0,,and it doesn’t cover the actual text.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:38:11.74,0:38:15.51,Default,,0,0,0,,The ability to back it up \Nso you can restore it to another device, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:38:15.51,0:38:17.51,Default,,0,0,0,,that’s going to be really helpful.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:38:17.51,0:38:18.55,Default,,0,0,0,,I love it!\N
Dialogue: 0,0:38:18.55,0:38:19.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Amazing!\N
Dialogue: 0,0:38:19.51,0:38:20.68,Default,,0,0,0,,OK. \NGo ahead.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:38:20.68,0:38:22.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah. \NGo ahead!\N
Dialogue: 0,0:38:22.52,0:38:24.00,Default,,0,0,0,,So you’re telling us we can proceed.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:38:25.19,0:38:26.45,Default,,0,0,0,,That’s fantastic! \N
Dialogue: 0,0:38:26.45,0:38:29.12,Default,,0,0,0,,But, brothers, you can’t show us \Nsomething like that \N
Dialogue: 0,0:38:29.12,0:38:32.26,Default,,0,0,0,,and not tell us when \Nwe’re going to get it.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:38:32.26,0:38:34.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, we said on the website \Nthat it was coming soon.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:38:34.13,0:38:37.00,Default,,0,0,0,,I know you said that on the website, \Nbut when?\N
Dialogue: 0,0:38:37.00,0:38:38.77,Default,,0,0,0,,Is it OK to be more specific than that?\N
Dialogue: 0,0:38:38.77,0:38:40.53,Default,,0,0,0,,I think that’s why they invited us here.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:38:40.53,0:38:42.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Paul, let’s hear it.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:38:42.64,0:38:44.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, we’re happy to tell you \Nthat the notes feature \N
Dialogue: 0,0:38:44.27,0:38:46.61,Default,,0,0,0,,in JW Library \Nwill be coming soon, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:38:46.61,0:38:51.05,Default,,0,0,0,,and by soon we mean \Nduring May of 2017—this month! \N
Dialogue: 0,0:38:51.05,0:38:54.95,Default,,0,0,0,,So we can go and check \Nthe app stores for an update.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:38:54.95,0:38:56.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, that’s wonderful to hear. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:38:56.78,0:38:59.65,Default,,0,0,0,,So all of us will be happy \Nto be able to put our own reminders \N
Dialogue: 0,0:38:59.65,0:39:03.02,Default,,0,0,0,,right there in the JW Library app. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:39:03.02,0:39:06.73,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, I’m looking forward \Nto being able to do that as well. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:39:06.73,0:39:08.70,Default,,0,0,0,,But now, \Nwhile I’ve got you here, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:39:08.70,0:39:12.00,Default,,0,0,0,,we’re not going to let you go \Nuntil we ask this big question: \N
Dialogue: 0,0:39:12.00,0:39:14.64,Default,,0,0,0,,What are you working on now? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:39:14.64,0:39:19.67,Default,,0,0,0,,In other words, what can we expect \Nto see soon with JW Library?\N
Dialogue: 0,0:39:19.67,0:39:22.64,Default,,0,0,0,,We have another brief video showing \Nwhat the team is working on \N
Dialogue: 0,0:39:22.64,0:39:26.11,Default,,0,0,0,,to support the Study Bible \Non the JW Library app. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:39:26.11,0:39:26.91,Default,,0,0,0,,Would you like to see it?\N
Dialogue: 0,0:39:26.91,0:39:28.00,Default,,0,0,0,,That’s wonderful. \NLet’s have a look.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:39:30.75,0:39:32.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Later this year, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:39:32.02,0:39:34.76,Default,,0,0,0,,work will begin on adding\Nthe Study Edition\N
Dialogue: 0,0:39:34.76,0:39:37.63,Default,,0,0,0,,of the New World Translation\Nto JW Library. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:39:37.63,0:39:39.43,Default,,0,0,0,,When this edition becomes available\N
Dialogue: 0,0:39:39.43,0:39:40.66,Default,,0,0,0,,in your language, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:39:40.66,0:39:42.26,Default,,0,0,0,,you will be able to discover\N
Dialogue: 0,0:39:42.26,0:39:44.30,Default,,0,0,0,,spiritual gems in the study notes.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:39:44.30,0:39:46.10,Default,,0,0,0,,And the new media gallery \N
Dialogue: 0,0:39:46.10,0:39:49.10,Default,,0,0,0,,will help you\Nto visualize the people, places, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:39:49.10,0:39:50.70,Default,,0,0,0,,and things you read about. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:39:50.70,0:39:53.77,Default,,0,0,0,,You will also see\Nthe new overviews of each book, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:39:53.77,0:39:55.44,Default,,0,0,0,,play the introductory videos, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:39:55.44,0:39:58.15,Default,,0,0,0,,and study additional appendix material.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:39:58.15,0:39:59.55,Default,,0,0,0,,All of this and more\N
Dialogue: 0,0:39:59.55,0:40:02.00,Default,,0,0,0,,is coming soon to JW Library!\N
Dialogue: 0,0:40:03.55,0:40:06.29,Default,,0,0,0,,That sounds so exciting. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:40:06.29,0:40:08.29,Default,,0,0,0,,So we’ll all look forward \Nto getting that feature. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:40:08.29,0:40:11.26,Default,,0,0,0,,You said, “coming soon,” didn’t you? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:40:11.26,0:40:13.66,Default,,0,0,0,,Anyway, \Nwe’d like to thank you very much \N
Dialogue: 0,0:40:13.66,0:40:17.03,Default,,0,0,0,,for the fact that you’ve come along \Nand you’ve explained so much to us \N
Dialogue: 0,0:40:17.03,0:40:20.13,Default,,0,0,0,,about what goes on \Nwith MEPS Programming \N
Dialogue: 0,0:40:20.13,0:40:22.20,Default,,0,0,0,,and the JW Library app. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:40:22.20,0:40:24.04,Default,,0,0,0,,But before you go, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:40:24.04,0:40:27.24,Default,,0,0,0,,we’d like to ask you, \Nwhen you go back to your department, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:40:27.24,0:40:30.44,Default,,0,0,0,,please, take an expression \Nof our appreciation \N
Dialogue: 0,0:40:30.44,0:40:32.95,Default,,0,0,0,,back to the hard-working \Nbrothers and sisters \N
Dialogue: 0,0:40:32.95,0:40:36.58,Default,,0,0,0,,who are working behind the scenes \Nin providing this tool for us.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:40:36.58,0:40:37.25,Default,,0,0,0,,Will do.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:40:37.25,0:40:37.89,Default,,0,0,0,,Happy to.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:40:37.89,0:40:38.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Thanks.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:40:38.19,0:40:40.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you very much.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:40:40.42,0:40:43.12,Default,,0,0,0,,And speaking of behind the scenes, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:40:43.12,0:40:45.36,Default,,0,0,0,,do you remember the beautiful dramas \N
Dialogue: 0,0:40:45.36,0:40:48.20,Default,,0,0,0,,we had at the regional convention \Nlast year? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:40:48.20,0:40:51.20,Default,,0,0,0,,One of them was \Nabout King Hezekiah. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:40:51.20,0:40:54.94,Default,,0,0,0,,We saw not only \Nthe threat Jehovah’s people faced \N
Dialogue: 0,0:40:54.94,0:40:58.21,Default,,0,0,0,,but also the protection \NJehovah provided. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:40:58.21,0:41:00.31,Default,,0,0,0,,In producing the drama, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:41:00.31,0:41:04.91,Default,,0,0,0,,the Audio/Video Services Department \Nused a lot of visual effects. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:41:04.91,0:41:09.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Let’s go behind the scenes \Nand find out what the work entailed.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:41:16.39,0:41:19.13,Default,,0,0,0,,The goal of our visual effects team \N
Dialogue: 0,0:41:19.13,0:41:22.83,Default,,0,0,0,,is to take the work done \Nduring film production and expand it. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:41:22.83,0:41:26.33,Default,,0,0,0,,Our work was driven by the Bible account.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:41:26.33,0:41:28.44,Default,,0,0,0,,The audience needed to feel \N
Dialogue: 0,0:41:28.44,0:41:30.91,Default,,0,0,0,,the intimidating power of the Assyrian army\N
Dialogue: 0,0:41:30.91,0:41:33.67,Default,,0,0,0,,while not endangering our actors.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:41:33.67,0:41:36.44,Default,,0,0,0,,And the use of visual effects \Nhad the added benefit \N
Dialogue: 0,0:41:36.44,0:41:39.00,Default,,0,0,0,,of drastically saving donated funds.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:41:40.55,0:41:45.05,Default,,0,0,0,,But this meant creating hundreds \N of digital arrows, war machines, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:41:45.05,0:41:48.12,Default,,0,0,0,,cities, tents, soldiers, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:41:48.12,0:41:50.52,Default,,0,0,0,,and even an Assyrian palace.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:41:50.52,0:41:52.96,Default,,0,0,0,,In some cases, the foreground elements \N
Dialogue: 0,0:41:52.96,0:41:55.06,Default,,0,0,0,,had to be separated \Nfrom the background \N
Dialogue: 0,0:41:55.06,0:41:58.90,Default,,0,0,0,,so digital components could be added.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:41:58.90,0:42:01.67,Default,,0,0,0,,This was a time-consuming process, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:42:01.67,0:42:05.97,Default,,0,0,0,,as many foreground elements \Nhad to be cut out frame by frame, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:42:05.97,0:42:09.00,Default,,0,0,0,,24 times for each second of video.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:42:10.11,0:42:12.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Our research team ensured \Nthat the world created \N
Dialogue: 0,0:42:12.65,0:42:14.68,Default,,0,0,0,,was as accurate as possible. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:42:14.68,0:42:15.82,Default,,0,0,0,,For example, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:42:15.82,0:42:18.52,Default,,0,0,0,,having period-correct materials \Nfor the temple \N
Dialogue: 0,0:42:18.52,0:42:21.59,Default,,0,0,0,,as well as accurate stone reliefs.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:42:21.59,0:42:23.26,Default,,0,0,0,,After filming was complete, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:42:23.26,0:42:25.93,Default,,0,0,0,,the research team noted \Nsome scenes in the treasury \N
Dialogue: 0,0:42:25.93,0:42:29.00,Default,,0,0,0,,were accidentally shot \Nshowing priests wearing sandals. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:42:31.10,0:42:33.03,Default,,0,0,0,,As this was inaccurate, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:42:33.03,0:42:36.77,Default,,0,0,0,,the issue was corrected \Nby generating additional digital treasures \N
Dialogue: 0,0:42:36.77,0:42:39.00,Default,,0,0,0,,and placing them in the foreground.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:42:40.57,0:42:44.68,Default,,0,0,0,,As we didn’t have \Nthe luxury of 185,000 extras, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:42:44.68,0:42:48.85,Default,,0,0,0,,actors were dressed in ancient costumes \N and their pictures were taken. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:42:48.85,0:42:52.19,Default,,0,0,0,,We then used these pictures \Nto create digital extras, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:42:52.19,0:42:54.19,Default,,0,0,0,,using crowd-simulating software \N
Dialogue: 0,0:42:54.19,0:42:58.00,Default,,0,0,0,,to place them in the scenes \Nand drive their movements.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:42:59.73,0:43:03.26,Default,,0,0,0,,The angel shot proved to be \None of the most challenging. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:43:03.26,0:43:08.00,Default,,0,0,0,,The original version didn’t have \Nthe dramatic feel needed for the scene.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:43:09.04,0:43:11.51,Default,,0,0,0,,So the entire sequence was recreated \N
Dialogue: 0,0:43:11.51,0:43:14.07,Default,,0,0,0,,to more accurately convey \Nthe immense power \N
Dialogue: 0,0:43:14.07,0:43:17.00,Default,,0,0,0,,that those present must have witnessed.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:43:19.75,0:43:23.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Finishing this project \Non schedule had many challenges. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:43:23.72,0:43:26.12,Default,,0,0,0,,After hearing about just a few of them, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:43:26.12,0:43:27.96,Default,,0,0,0,,one industry expert said \N
Dialogue: 0,0:43:27.96,0:43:30.62,Default,,0,0,0,,what we were attempting was impossible.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:43:30.62,0:43:33.76,Default,,0,0,0,,But like Hezekiah \Nwhen hearing negative reports, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:43:33.76,0:43:36.70,Default,,0,0,0,,we stayed positive \Nand relied on Jehovah.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:43:36.70,0:43:40.03,Default,,0,0,0,,With His help, \Nthe film was completed on time \N
Dialogue: 0,0:43:40.03,0:43:45.84,Default,,0,0,0,,and is now a wonderful tool \Nto bring this Bible account to life.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:43:45.84,0:43:47.91,Default,,0,0,0,,A beautiful drama, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:43:47.91,0:43:49.94,Default,,0,0,0,,and how encouraging it was \N
Dialogue: 0,0:43:49.94,0:43:52.78,Default,,0,0,0,,to see Jehovah rescue his people! \N
Dialogue: 0,0:43:52.78,0:43:56.82,Default,,0,0,0,,The 2016 regional convention \Nwas excellent, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:43:56.82,0:43:58.62,Default,,0,0,0,,don’t you agree? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:43:58.62,0:44:02.46,Default,,0,0,0,,But you’ll be happy to know \Nthat we have prepared a little glimpse \N
Dialogue: 0,0:44:02.46,0:44:05.46,Default,,0,0,0,,of what is to come \Nat this year’s convention \N
Dialogue: 0,0:44:05.46,0:44:07.00,Default,,0,0,0,,to whet your appetite.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:44:10.36,0:44:11.83,Default,,0,0,0,,Are you OK?\N
Dialogue: 0,0:44:11.83,0:44:13.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Brian, I’m worried.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:44:13.27,0:44:15.27,Default,,0,0,0,,You need more money.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:44:15.27,0:44:16.74,Default,,0,0,0,,Jehovah will take care of us. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:44:16.74,0:44:18.71,Default,,0,0,0,,He always has. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:44:18.71,0:44:20.61,Default,,0,0,0,,We have enough.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:44:20.61,0:44:22.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Maybe enough for today, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:44:22.11,0:44:24.85,Default,,0,0,0,,but what if you get sick?\N
Dialogue: 0,0:44:24.85,0:44:27.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Gloria’s mother keeps badgering her \Nand me to move up.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:44:28.12,0:44:30.18,Default,,0,0,0,,I can get a job \Nat my uncle’s real estate firm. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:44:30.18,0:44:33.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Maybe this is an answer \Nto our prayers.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:44:34.12,0:44:36.29,Default,,0,0,0,,What about your pioneering?\N
Dialogue: 0,0:44:36.29,0:44:38.00,Default,,0,0,0,,What about it? \NI can do both.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:44:39.13,0:44:41.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Gloria, I must congratulate you \N
Dialogue: 0,0:44:41.46,0:44:44.43,Default,,0,0,0,,on your hard work with my company.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:44:44.43,0:44:47.00,Default,,0,0,0,,But you must learn \Nto keep your religion in its place.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:44:48.80,0:44:53.07,Default,,0,0,0,,We’re neglecting \Nfamily worship, study, service. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:44:53.07,0:44:55.31,Default,,0,0,0,,We’ve even become too busy, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:44:55.31,0:44:58.00,Default,,0,0,0,,or maybe too ashamed, \Nto even pray together.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:44:59.48,0:45:01.08,Default,,0,0,0,,I’m concerned about you.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:45:01.08,0:45:03.38,Default,,0,0,0,,One of the things \Nthat you always talked to me about \N
Dialogue: 0,0:45:03.38,0:45:06.09,Default,,0,0,0,,was Matthew 6:24: \N
Dialogue: 0,0:45:06.09,0:45:08.82,Default,,0,0,0,,‘You cannot slave for God and for Riches.’\N
Dialogue: 0,0:45:08.82,0:45:12.00,Default,,0,0,0,,You’re not the same person \Nthat I once knew.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:45:14.03,0:45:15.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Dad, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:45:15.76,0:45:17.06,Default,,0,0,0,,where is Mom?\N
Dialogue: 0,0:45:17.06,0:45:21.00,Default,,0,0,0,,She is coming, right?\N
Dialogue: 0,0:45:22.30,0:45:24.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Is it really wrong \N
Dialogue: 0,0:45:24.34,0:45:26.00,Default,,0,0,0,,to try to improve our life?\N
Dialogue: 0,0:45:27.34,0:45:28.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Mom. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:45:28.88,0:45:30.21,Default,,0,0,0,,“Remember the wife of Lot.”\N
Dialogue: 0,0:45:30.21,0:45:31.04,Default,,0,0,0,,“Remember the wife of Lot.”\N
Dialogue: 0,0:45:31.04,0:45:34.00,Default,,0,0,0,,“Remember the wife of Lot.”\N
Dialogue: 0,0:45:40.39,0:45:42.62,Default,,0,0,0,,If you have yet to make definite plans \N
Dialogue: 0,0:45:42.62,0:45:45.06,Default,,0,0,0,,to attend your regional convention this year,\N
Dialogue: 0,0:45:45.06,0:45:46.86,Default,,0,0,0,,don’t delay. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:45:46.86,0:45:50.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Our conventions are a loving provision \Nfrom Jehovah. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:45:50.16,0:45:52.17,Default,,0,0,0,,Whatever it takes\N
Dialogue: 0,0:45:52.17,0:45:54.64,Default,,0,0,0,,—talking to your boss to get time off work \N
Dialogue: 0,0:45:54.64,0:45:56.47,Default,,0,0,0,,or making travel plans—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:45:56.47,0:46:00.27,Default,,0,0,0,,yes, whatever it takes, \Nour efforts are worth it \N
Dialogue: 0,0:46:00.27,0:46:04.21,Default,,0,0,0,,because we truly treasure \NJehovah’s reminders.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:46:04.21,0:46:07.01,Default,,0,0,0,,Jesus’ words \Nat Matthew 11:28 \N
Dialogue: 0,0:46:07.01,0:46:09.48,Default,,0,0,0,,are very appropriate \Nconsidering everything \N
Dialogue: 0,0:46:09.48,0:46:12.29,Default,,0,0,0,,we go through \Nin this system of things: \N
Dialogue: 0,0:46:12.29,0:46:16.79,Default,,0,0,0,,“Come to me, all you who \Nare toiling and loaded down, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:46:16.79,0:46:18.99,Default,,0,0,0,,and I will refresh you.” \N
Dialogue: 0,0:46:18.99,0:46:22.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, conventions \Ncan be of refreshment to us, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:46:22.63,0:46:25.07,Default,,0,0,0,,giving us the boost we need. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:46:25.07,0:46:28.10,Default,,0,0,0,,But such refreshment \Nis also available \N
Dialogue: 0,0:46:28.10,0:46:31.44,Default,,0,0,0,,when the world around us \Nseems to be falling apart. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:46:31.44,0:46:35.08,Default,,0,0,0,,How does the organization \Nhelp our brothers and sisters  \N
Dialogue: 0,0:46:35.08,0:46:37.51,Default,,0,0,0,,in times of national crisis? \N
Dialogue: 0,0:46:37.51,0:46:41.98,Default,,0,0,0,,We met two Witness couples\Nwho personally experienced \N
Dialogue: 0,0:46:41.98,0:46:45.00,Default,,0,0,0,,two of the largest terrorist attacks \Nin recent years.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:46:52.26,0:46:54.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Not a day goes by \Nwhen we don’t think \N
Dialogue: 0,0:46:54.86,0:46:57.00,Default,,0,0,0,,about our son, Paulie.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:47:06.07,0:47:08.88,Default,,0,0,0,,There was horror and suffering, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:47:08.88,0:47:11.00,Default,,0,0,0,,things we don’t want to witness anymore.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:47:22.16,0:47:28.00,Default,,0,0,0,,September 11 \Nwas a very scary, terrifying day.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:47:29.06,0:47:31.37,Default,,0,0,0,,As for me, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:47:31.37,0:47:34.54,Default,,0,0,0,,when I really understood \Nwhat was happening, I got scared. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:47:34.54,0:47:36.10,Default,,0,0,0,,I didn’t know what to do. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:47:36.10,0:47:38.04,Default,,0,0,0,,I didn’t know what to think. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:47:38.04,0:47:41.48,Default,,0,0,0,,I felt helpless.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:47:41.48,0:47:44.38,Default,,0,0,0,,When the second tower fell, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:47:44.38,0:47:47.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Paulie was on the 110th floor \N
Dialogue: 0,0:47:47.28,0:47:50.62,Default,,0,0,0,,and everybody was shouting, crying. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:47:50.62,0:47:53.12,Default,,0,0,0,,I was praying to Jehovah \N
Dialogue: 0,0:47:53.12,0:47:56.00,Default,,0,0,0,,because I was heartbroken.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:48:00.09,0:48:03.66,Default,,0,0,0,,We live on Voltaire Boulevard; \N it’s a broad avenue. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:48:03.66,0:48:06.67,Default,,0,0,0,,There is a concert hall called the Bataclan. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:48:06.67,0:48:09.30,Default,,0,0,0,,When the doors of the Bataclan are open, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:48:09.30,0:48:13.00,Default,,0,0,0,,we can hear everything that goes on inside.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:48:15.84,0:48:19.01,Default,,0,0,0,,That night, three men \Nentered the Bataclan concert hall, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:48:19.01,0:48:22.88,Default,,0,0,0,,and they started shooting into the crowd. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:48:22.88,0:48:24.99,Default,,0,0,0,,We immediately grabbed our “go bag.” \N
Dialogue: 0,0:48:24.99,0:48:27.79,Default,,0,0,0,,And then we sat in front of the sofa, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:48:27.79,0:48:30.46,Default,,0,0,0,,and we begged Jehovah for his holy spirit \N
Dialogue: 0,0:48:30.46,0:48:33.00,Default,,0,0,0,,so we could face the situation.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:48:42.20,0:48:45.87,Default,,0,0,0,,It was around 10:00 p.m. \Nwhen there was a news flash \N
Dialogue: 0,0:48:45.87,0:48:48.74,Default,,0,0,0,,that announced that there was an attack. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:48:48.74,0:48:51.00,Default,,0,0,0,,I was in shock when I heard the news, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:48:52.18,0:48:56.00,Default,,0,0,0,,and then I immediately thought \Nabout our brothers and sisters. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:48:58.05,0:49:01.72,Default,,0,0,0,,I quickly got in contact \Nwith the circuit overseer \N
Dialogue: 0,0:49:01.72,0:49:05.33,Default,,0,0,0,,in order to get some news \Nabout our brothers and sisters, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:49:05.33,0:49:07.69,Default,,0,0,0,,to know how they were doing. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:49:07.69,0:49:09.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Then, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:49:09.53,0:49:11.26,Default,,0,0,0,,very early the next morning, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:49:11.26,0:49:14.70,Default,,0,0,0,,we set up an emergency committee \Nmade up of several brothers \N
Dialogue: 0,0:49:14.70,0:49:16.70,Default,,0,0,0,,from the Service Department. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:49:16.70,0:49:20.37,Default,,0,0,0,,We decided to write a letter \Nand make other arrangements \N
Dialogue: 0,0:49:20.37,0:49:23.28,Default,,0,0,0,,to assist the friends who, \Nin one way or another, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:49:23.28,0:49:26.58,Default,,0,0,0,,were affected by this event. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:49:26.58,0:49:27.75,Default,,0,0,0,,In turn, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:49:27.75,0:49:30.22,Default,,0,0,0,,the circuit overseer \Nwould make an effort \N
Dialogue: 0,0:49:30.22,0:49:33.32,Default,,0,0,0,,to rapidly get in touch \Nwith the elders \N
Dialogue: 0,0:49:33.32,0:49:36.00,Default,,0,0,0,,who oversee \Nthe affected territory.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:49:39.76,0:49:42.80,Default,,0,0,0,,One of our challenges, on a personal level, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:49:42.80,0:49:44.87,Default,,0,0,0,,was whether we would even be able \N
Dialogue: 0,0:49:44.87,0:49:46.93,Default,,0,0,0,,to encourage our brothers and sisters \N
Dialogue: 0,0:49:46.93,0:49:50.47,Default,,0,0,0,,because we had never experienced \Nsuch a terrible event. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:49:50.47,0:49:52.54,Default,,0,0,0,,We organized ourselves; \N
Dialogue: 0,0:49:52.54,0:49:55.00,Default,,0,0,0,,we paired up as elders \Nand headed off to do shepherding.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:49:56.58,0:50:00.31,Default,,0,0,0,,We started calling midmorning \Non Tuesday. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:50:00.31,0:50:02.05,Default,,0,0,0,,We received a report back \N
Dialogue: 0,0:50:02.05,0:50:03.88,Default,,0,0,0,,from all the traveling overseers \N
Dialogue: 0,0:50:03.88,0:50:05.12,Default,,0,0,0,,by the end of Thursday. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:50:05.12,0:50:07.32,Default,,0,0,0,,And unfortunately, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:50:07.32,0:50:10.16,Default,,0,0,0,,we learned that 14 \Nof our brothers and sisters \N
Dialogue: 0,0:50:10.16,0:50:13.69,Default,,0,0,0,,had lost their lives. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:50:13.69,0:50:18.80,Default,,0,0,0,,We knew that we needed \Nto encourage the families; \N
Dialogue: 0,0:50:18.80,0:50:22.97,Default,,0,0,0,,we knew that we needed \Nto shepherd them as soon as possible.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:50:22.97,0:50:26.77,Default,,0,0,0,,The elders immediately came. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:50:26.77,0:50:29.11,Default,,0,0,0,,We went over the book of Job, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:50:29.11,0:50:31.61,Default,,0,0,0,,and I just listened. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:50:31.61,0:50:33.55,Default,,0,0,0,,You know, I was just listening. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:50:33.55,0:50:36.45,Default,,0,0,0,,I’ve heard the same words before, \Nbut it was different now. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:50:36.45,0:50:40.00,Default,,0,0,0,,The things that were being said \Nwent straight to my heart.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:50:42.26,0:50:45.76,Default,,0,0,0,,A few days later, we were visited \Nby two brothers from Bethel. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:50:45.76,0:50:49.00,Default,,0,0,0,,It was very touching \Nthat they came to see us \N
Dialogue: 0,0:50:49.00,0:50:51.30,Default,,0,0,0,,and that they \Nwere concerned about us. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:50:51.30,0:50:56.17,Default,,0,0,0,,It shows us that Jehovah \Nwas aware of how we felt that night.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:50:56.17,0:50:58.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Our brothers were there. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:50:58.61,0:51:01.11,Default,,0,0,0,,They were ready \Nto help one another out. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:51:01.11,0:51:05.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Then there was \Nso much empathy and love shown.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:51:05.08,0:51:06.91,Default,,0,0,0,,When we were ultimately granted \N
Dialogue: 0,0:51:06.91,0:51:08.75,Default,,0,0,0,,access to ground zero \N
Dialogue: 0,0:51:08.75,0:51:11.49,Default,,0,0,0,,and we started encountering \N
Dialogue: 0,0:51:11.49,0:51:13.42,Default,,0,0,0,,the first responders, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:51:13.42,0:51:16.66,Default,,0,0,0,,we let them know how much \Nwe appreciated their hard work \N
Dialogue: 0,0:51:16.66,0:51:18.66,Default,,0,0,0,,and that they had a skill set \N
Dialogue: 0,0:51:18.66,0:51:20.56,Default,,0,0,0,,that we didn’t have. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:51:20.56,0:51:21.93,Default,,0,0,0,,But yet our skill set \N
Dialogue: 0,0:51:21.93,0:51:24.66,Default,,0,0,0,,was trying \Nto offer comfort to them. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:51:24.66,0:51:27.27,Default,,0,0,0,,We shared a scripture with them. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:51:27.27,0:51:30.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Immediately, we could tell \Nthat that was something \N
Dialogue: 0,0:51:30.10,0:51:33.57,Default,,0,0,0,,that caused emotion \Nto rise up in them right away. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:51:33.57,0:51:35.98,Default,,0,0,0,,And they expressed \N
Dialogue: 0,0:51:35.98,0:51:37.38,Default,,0,0,0,,great appreciation for that. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:51:37.38,0:51:40.61,Default,,0,0,0,,It’s one of the beautiful things \Nabout the Scriptures\N
Dialogue: 0,0:51:40.61,0:51:44.65,Default,,0,0,0,,—that they’re calming, \Nsoothing, comforting. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:51:44.65,0:51:47.52,Default,,0,0,0,,And the Scriptures \Ndid not let down the workers \N
Dialogue: 0,0:51:47.52,0:51:50.00,Default,,0,0,0,,that were there at ground zero either.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:51:51.79,0:51:54.80,Default,,0,0,0,,The visit of the brothers \Nfrom Bethel was really \N
Dialogue: 0,0:51:54.80,0:51:56.83,Default,,0,0,0,,a gift from Jehovah. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:51:56.83,0:51:59.53,Default,,0,0,0,,It showed his genuine interest in us. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:51:59.53,0:52:02.00,Default,,0,0,0,,It was really wonderful.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:52:03.64,0:52:05.61,Default,,0,0,0,,After the brothers visited us, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:52:05.61,0:52:07.71,Default,,0,0,0,,we felt so comforted, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:52:07.71,0:52:09.44,Default,,0,0,0,,so encouraged, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:52:09.44,0:52:11.24,Default,,0,0,0,,that we said to each other: \N
Dialogue: 0,0:52:11.24,0:52:14.65,Default,,0,0,0,,“We have to get back in the ministry \N
Dialogue: 0,0:52:14.65,0:52:16.65,Default,,0,0,0,,“and comfort people in the territory. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:52:16.65,0:52:20.00,Default,,0,0,0,,We have to console \Nour brothers and sisters as well.” \N
Dialogue: 0,0:52:21.29,0:52:23.76,Default,,0,0,0,,We can only thank and glorify Jehovah, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:52:23.76,0:52:25.00,Default,,0,0,0,,who really is a God of love.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:52:31.60,0:52:33.77,Default,,0,0,0,,I kind of felt \N
Dialogue: 0,0:52:33.77,0:52:36.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Jehovah’s hand just reaching out to me, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:52:36.27,0:52:39.64,Default,,0,0,0,,which I needed. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:52:39.64,0:52:43.84,Default,,0,0,0,,But I cannot wait till the day \Nthat I’m totally refreshed. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:52:43.84,0:52:46.81,Default,,0,0,0,,Where I can see, \N I can actually see, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:52:46.81,0:52:48.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Paulie. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:52:48.62,0:52:51.22,Default,,0,0,0,,I can see him just coming back \N
Dialogue: 0,0:52:51.22,0:52:53.25,Default,,0,0,0,,into our lives, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:52:53.25,0:52:56.00,Default,,0,0,0,,and I want to embrace him so much.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:52:59.03,0:53:03.73,Default,,0,0,0,,After something like this, \Nwe are not the same. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:53:03.73,0:53:05.00,Default,,0,0,0,,But \N
Dialogue: 0,0:53:06.87,0:53:09.90,Default,,0,0,0,,with the help of the organization\N
Dialogue: 0,0:53:09.90,0:53:11.61,Default,,0,0,0,,—the brothers—\N
Dialogue: 0,0:53:11.61,0:53:13.81,Default,,0,0,0,,Jehovah is there for us. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:53:13.81,0:53:15.58,Default,,0,0,0,,So that— \N
Dialogue: 0,0:53:15.58,0:53:18.91,Default,,0,0,0,,That is refreshing.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:53:18.91,0:53:20.91,Default,,0,0,0,,And I thank Jehovah a lot \N
Dialogue: 0,0:53:20.91,0:53:24.18,Default,,0,0,0,,for what he wants to do for me \N
Dialogue: 0,0:53:24.18,0:53:28.22,Default,,0,0,0,,and also for the millions of people \N
Dialogue: 0,0:53:28.22,0:53:31.00,Default,,0,0,0,,that feel the same way.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:53:35.66,0:53:37.66,Default,,0,0,0,,What these couples went through \N
Dialogue: 0,0:53:37.66,0:53:40.70,Default,,0,0,0,,was a horrible reminder of Satan’s rule, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:53:40.70,0:53:43.70,Default,,0,0,0,,but we look forward \Nto the relief from Jehovah\N
Dialogue: 0,0:53:43.70,0:53:46.27,Default,,0,0,0,,—the only true hope we have. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:53:46.27,0:53:50.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Reminders of Jehovah’s care, \Nsuch as these interviews, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:53:50.64,0:53:54.28,Default,,0,0,0,,can be ‘the joy of our heart,’ \Nas the psalmist said. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:53:54.28,0:53:57.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, “the reminder \Nof Jehovah is trustworthy, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:53:57.32,0:54:01.29,Default,,0,0,0,,making the inexperienced one wise.”\N
Dialogue: 0,0:54:01.29,0:54:03.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Before we conclude, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:54:03.32,0:54:07.49,Default,,0,0,0,,let’s visit our brothers \Nand sisters in India. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:54:07.49,0:54:10.66,Default,,0,0,0,,India is the second-most-populated country\Nin the world, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:54:10.66,0:54:15.20,Default,,0,0,0,,with a population \Nof some 1.2 billion people. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:54:15.20,0:54:18.24,Default,,0,0,0,,The Kingdom preaching work \Nis conducted \N
Dialogue: 0,0:54:18.24,0:54:21.17,Default,,0,0,0,,by some 45,000 brothers and sisters \N
Dialogue: 0,0:54:21.17,0:54:23.81,Default,,0,0,0,,in 627 congregations, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:54:23.81,0:54:25.91,Default,,0,0,0,,and last year, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:54:25.91,0:54:29.42,Default,,0,0,0,,close to 125,000 people attended \N
Dialogue: 0,0:54:29.42,0:54:32.62,Default,,0,0,0,,the Memorial of Christ’s death.\N
Dialogue: 0,0:54:32.62,0:54:35.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Our visit brings us to Peermedu, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:54:35.06,0:54:37.39,Default,,0,0,0,,which is located in the southern tip \N
Dialogue: 0,0:54:37.39,0:54:40.99,Default,,0,0,0,,of the Indian Peninsula, \Nin the state of Kerala. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:54:40.99,0:54:43.30,Default,,0,0,0,,This town is located \N
Dialogue: 0,0:54:43.30,0:54:48.00,Default,,0,0,0,,some 914 meters, \Nor almost 3,000 feet, above sea level. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:54:49.04,0:54:52.47,Default,,0,0,0,,It is a land of spices and lush greenery, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:54:52.47,0:54:55.74,Default,,0,0,0,,with tea and coffee plantations. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:54:55.74,0:54:59.00,Default,,0,0,0,,The two congregations \Nthere have a total of 70 publishers. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:55:01.15,0:55:03.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Many of them work in tea estates \N
Dialogue: 0,0:55:03.48,0:55:06.25,Default,,0,0,0,,and struggle to make a living. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:55:06.25,0:55:09.42,Default,,0,0,0,,They are eager users of the JW Library app, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:55:09.42,0:55:11.62,Default,,0,0,0,,which they use to share \Nour videos \N
Dialogue: 0,0:55:11.62,0:55:14.23,Default,,0,0,0,,and publications \Nin the ministry. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:55:14.23,0:55:17.96,Default,,0,0,0,,As Peermedu is a hill station, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:55:17.96,0:55:21.00,Default,,0,0,0,,their territory consists \Nof rugged and uneven terrain. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:55:23.97,0:55:25.97,Default,,0,0,0,,Since the congregations there are watching \N
Dialogue: 0,0:55:25.97,0:55:28.04,Default,,0,0,0,,this program together with all of us, \N
Dialogue: 0,0:55:28.04,0:55:30.58,Default,,0,0,0,,we wanted to take this opportunity \N
Dialogue: 0,0:55:30.58,0:55:33.45,Default,,0,0,0,,to convey their warm Christian greetings \N
Dialogue: 0,0:55:33.45,0:55:36.58,Default,,0,0,0,,to all of Jehovah’s people \Naround the world. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:55:36.58,0:55:39.02,Default,,0,0,0,,We love you very much. \N
Dialogue: 0,0:55:39.02,0:55:41.79,Default,,0,0,0,,This is JW Broadcasting \N
Dialogue: 0,0:55:41.79,0:55:44.07,Default,,0,0,0,,from the world headquarters \Nof Jehovah’s Witnesses.\N
